WEBVTT

00:13.317 --> 00:16.016
[gentle music]

00:47.699 --> 00:52.313
♪ This town's changed ♪

00:53.401 --> 00:57.753
♪ People rearrange ♪

00:58.884 --> 01:03.541
♪ It's not quite like ♪

01:03.628 --> 01:08.242
♪ Now there's raging at night ♪

01:09.808 --> 01:14.117
♪ But the morning's
much like you ♪

01:15.249 --> 01:17.816
♪ With its lavender hue ♪

01:56.072 --> 02:00.859
♪ These thoughts changed ♪

02:01.991 --> 02:06.648
♪ Feelings rearranged ♪

02:07.736 --> 02:12.436
♪ It's not fright like ♪

02:13.611 --> 02:17.876
♪ All that raging at night ♪

02:19.182 --> 02:23.969
♪ And now it's much past due ♪

02:25.057 --> 02:27.364
♪ All this lavender hue ♪

02:28.844 --> 02:31.586
- Mom, I'm gonna be late.

02:31.673 --> 02:35.285
- Since when are you in
a hurry to get to school?

02:35.372 --> 02:36.982
- I don't want detention.

02:37.069 --> 02:39.333
Drake and I are playing
"Hunters Watch" after school.

02:40.334 --> 02:41.900
- Boys.

02:44.338 --> 02:47.776
- Have you see my blue notebook,
the one with the spirals?

02:47.863 --> 02:49.299
- You are not making us
late for school again.

02:49.386 --> 02:51.127
- You put it in your
backpack at breakfast.

02:51.214 --> 02:52.650
- Oh yeah.

02:55.827 --> 02:56.741
- Your lunch.

02:56.828 --> 02:58.221
- Thanks.

02:58.308 --> 03:00.049
- It's 8:02, mom!

03:00.136 --> 03:01.137
- Hey.

03:01.224 --> 03:02.878
Yeah, I finished it.

03:02.965 --> 03:05.010
It was only 20 questions.

03:05.097 --> 03:07.143
- Okay, everybody in the car.

03:08.449 --> 03:09.928
Was anybody gonna tell me?

03:11.365 --> 03:12.148
Brennan.

03:14.933 --> 03:16.021
Okay, sure.

03:16.108 --> 03:17.197
I'll head that way now.

03:17.284 --> 03:18.633
Is this a 55A?

03:18.720 --> 03:19.460
- A homicide?

03:21.897 --> 03:24.073
- Okay, I'll be right there.

03:25.379 --> 03:27.076
- Someone died?

03:27.163 --> 03:29.600
- An elderly woman
up on Briar Rock.

03:29.687 --> 03:31.559
She's a mountain
woman, there's no ID.

03:31.646 --> 03:33.474
- There's still mountain
people living up there?

03:33.561 --> 03:35.432
- A few, as far as
anyone can tell.

03:35.519 --> 03:36.390
- Why are you getting the call?

03:36.477 --> 03:38.043
- The store manager in town

03:38.130 --> 03:40.568
thinks she may have been
keeping a boy on her homestead.

03:40.655 --> 03:42.483
If so, he's up there all alone.

03:42.570 --> 03:43.832
- Well then you better hurry.

03:43.919 --> 03:45.225
I'll run the kids to school.

03:45.312 --> 03:46.748
- What about your
writing deadline?

03:46.835 --> 03:48.140
- It's all up here.

03:48.228 --> 03:49.620
Typing it out as
just a formality.

03:49.707 --> 03:50.447
- Thank you.

03:54.103 --> 03:54.930
- I'm gonna be late.

03:55.017 --> 03:56.018
- And I'm gone.

03:56.105 --> 03:57.237
Good luck finding the boy.

03:57.324 --> 03:58.716
- [Janelle] If there is one.

04:01.066 --> 04:02.981
- Store manager said
she ordered her supplies

04:03.068 --> 04:05.070
under the name of the
Lila Mae Whittaker.

04:05.157 --> 04:06.115
- So we have an ID then?

04:06.202 --> 04:08.944
- It could be an alias.

04:09.031 --> 04:11.120
He also had an order
from Nathaniel Hawthorne.

04:11.207 --> 04:14.123
Coroner's best guess is
she was in her mid 80's.

04:14.210 --> 04:16.517
- So why are we
assuming she had a kid?

04:16.604 --> 04:18.954
- She ordered a copy
of "Tom Sawyer".

04:19.041 --> 04:20.608
- [Janelle] So she likes Twain.

04:20.695 --> 04:24.002
- And a pair of size
10 male work boots.

04:24.089 --> 04:26.091
- The storekeeper is
quite the detective.

04:26.178 --> 04:27.658
He should come work for us.

04:27.745 --> 04:29.094
- Well, this may all
be a wild goose chase,

04:29.181 --> 04:30.966
but if we suspect
there's a minor involved,

04:31.053 --> 04:32.272
we have to check it out.

04:33.708 --> 04:34.970
- We sure this is
the right path?

04:35.057 --> 04:36.232
- I have no idea.

04:37.277 --> 04:38.626
According to the chopper survey,

04:38.713 --> 04:40.105
there's supposed to be
a thick cluster of trees

04:40.192 --> 04:42.369
over that ridge there
that could cover a house.

04:42.456 --> 04:43.370
Let's check it out.

04:46.677 --> 04:47.417
- Hold on.

04:49.680 --> 04:51.203
You better come look at this.

04:53.380 --> 04:54.555
- Well, I'll be.

04:56.078 --> 04:57.732
Jeremiah Whittaker.

04:57.819 --> 05:00.256
Could be the husband,
this isn't new.

05:00.343 --> 05:01.866
Let's keep moving.

05:01.953 --> 05:03.346
Keep your eyes open.

05:03.433 --> 05:04.782
Most people up
here are friendly,

05:04.869 --> 05:06.828
but a few wave hello
with their shotguns.

05:09.091 --> 05:11.572
[gentle music]

05:17.491 --> 05:20.058
[ominous music]

05:40.731 --> 05:41.993
- Sheriff's department.

05:42.080 --> 05:43.081
Anyone home?

05:48.478 --> 05:49.261
Hello?

05:51.263 --> 05:53.744
- We don't have a
warrant to go in.

05:53.831 --> 05:55.006
Let's comb the property.

05:57.313 --> 06:00.142
[ominous music]

06:07.454 --> 06:10.108
There's definitely
someone living here.

06:10.195 --> 06:13.068
[ominous music]

06:13.155 --> 06:14.069
Brennan.

06:14.156 --> 06:15.157
- On it.

06:15.984 --> 06:18.682
[dramatic music]

06:49.844 --> 06:51.759
It's a male between 15 and 18.

06:51.846 --> 06:53.195
He just vanished.

06:53.282 --> 06:54.457
- All right, I'll
head down this way.

06:54.544 --> 06:56.154
He may cut back to the cabin.

06:56.241 --> 06:57.373
- I'll do a sweep here and
meet you back up the hill.

06:57.460 --> 06:58.809
- Be careful.

06:58.896 --> 07:00.289
We have no idea what
this kid is like.

07:00.376 --> 07:02.160
Don't hesitate to defend
yourself if you have to.

07:03.248 --> 07:06.077
[ominous music]

07:20.048 --> 07:21.092
- You gave me quite
a chase there.

07:22.572 --> 07:24.008
My name is Deputy Brennan.

07:24.095 --> 07:26.054
I'm with the County
Sheriff's department.

07:26.141 --> 07:27.055
We need to talk.

07:28.056 --> 07:29.666
I'm not here to hurt you.

07:29.753 --> 07:31.755
I just need to make
sure you're all right.

07:33.540 --> 07:35.455
Any chance you could
come out of there?

07:39.241 --> 07:41.243
Do you know a Lila
Mae Whittaker?

07:43.288 --> 07:45.029
- Yes.

07:45.116 --> 07:46.074
- Is she your grandmother?

07:47.205 --> 07:49.077
- No, she looks after me though.

07:51.122 --> 07:52.863
- There's no easy
way to say this.

07:54.299 --> 07:55.779
- She passed, didn't she?

07:57.085 --> 07:58.260
- I'm afraid so.

07:59.217 --> 08:00.131
Are you here alone?

08:02.873 --> 08:04.353
- Pap passed awhile back.

08:06.703 --> 08:08.749
- I found this wooden bird.

08:11.229 --> 08:12.492
I think maybe you dropped it.

08:19.194 --> 08:20.848
It's beautiful.

08:20.935 --> 08:21.675
Did you make it?

08:23.894 --> 08:24.895
- It's gran's.

08:26.157 --> 08:28.377
Pap whittled it for her.

08:28.464 --> 08:30.205
- What about your mom or dad?

08:30.292 --> 08:31.859
They ever come around?

08:31.946 --> 08:33.034
- No, I ain't never,

08:34.339 --> 08:36.994
I haven't ever seen them.

08:37.081 --> 08:38.605
- [Callier] Brennan,
have you spotted him?

08:38.692 --> 08:39.606
- Oh, it's okay.

08:39.693 --> 08:40.781
It's okay, it's just my radio.

08:42.043 --> 08:43.087
- I've read about radios.

08:45.133 --> 08:45.960
- Yeah, he's here.

08:47.309 --> 08:48.963
- On my way.

08:49.050 --> 08:50.617
- No, no, don't
come down just yet.

08:50.704 --> 08:52.009
We're talking.

08:52.096 --> 08:53.054
- [Callier] Are you good?

08:53.141 --> 08:54.664
- Yeah, he seems okay.

08:56.448 --> 08:58.407
- [Finch] Who are
you talking to?

08:58.494 --> 09:00.104
- The county sheriff.

09:00.191 --> 09:02.280
He's been helping
me look for you.

09:02.367 --> 09:04.195
- Does it play music, too?

09:04.282 --> 09:05.153
- My radio?

09:06.284 --> 09:07.590
No.

09:07.677 --> 09:09.113
No, it's not that
kind of a radio.

09:10.027 --> 09:10.941
Do you like music?

09:12.290 --> 09:13.335
My phone can play music.

09:16.120 --> 09:17.644
- Your telephone?

09:20.124 --> 09:20.908
- Yeah.

09:21.865 --> 09:22.562
See?

09:25.216 --> 09:25.913
- I don't see any wires.

09:27.436 --> 09:29.351
- Have you ever been off
this mountain before?

09:29.438 --> 09:30.874
- No, ma'am.

09:30.961 --> 09:33.616
My gran said if ever
I leave this mountain

09:33.703 --> 09:35.836
folks down below might
never let me come back.

09:37.228 --> 09:39.579
- You said you
read about radios.

09:39.666 --> 09:40.536
Do you like to read?

09:40.623 --> 09:42.146
- Yes, ma'am.

09:42.233 --> 09:45.106
I have books on a
shelf near my bed.

09:45.193 --> 09:47.978
I have bunches of
them, 12 in all.

09:48.065 --> 09:49.850
I've read them so many times,

09:49.937 --> 09:51.242
I can almost say them by rote,

09:52.330 --> 09:54.289
except'n the Bible.

09:54.376 --> 09:56.073
I'm still working
on learning it.

09:56.160 --> 09:58.336
Now that's a big one.

09:58.423 --> 10:01.731
But my gran wants me to
have that one right up here

10:01.818 --> 10:03.733
so that I can use it
whenever I need it.

10:04.647 --> 10:06.257
She promised me

10:06.344 --> 10:09.609
that when I finished reading
the whole thing cover to cover

10:09.696 --> 10:11.306
that she would
use her wool money

10:11.393 --> 10:13.525
to buy me a copy of Tom...

10:17.181 --> 10:18.052
- What's your name?

10:19.227 --> 10:20.228
- Finch.

10:20.315 --> 10:21.142
- Oh, like the bird.

10:22.926 --> 10:26.495
- My gran raised a baby bird
she found alone in the woods.

10:26.582 --> 10:28.497
She used to say that
when I was little,

10:28.584 --> 10:30.499
I reminded her of the finch.

10:30.586 --> 10:32.806
So that's where she got my name.

10:32.893 --> 10:36.505
- Look Finch, I'm
afraid it's time to go.

10:36.592 --> 10:39.987
- Oh, well thanks
for looking after me.

10:40.074 --> 10:42.076
Maybe you could come
visit'n again sometime.

10:42.163 --> 10:44.208
- No, no, that's
not what I mean.

10:44.295 --> 10:46.210
We're gonna need
you to come with us.

10:46.297 --> 10:47.734
- No, I'll be fine here.

10:47.821 --> 10:49.474
I can take care of myself.

10:49.561 --> 10:51.128
I like it here.

10:51.215 --> 10:54.654
- I know you do, but you see
I'm responsible for you now

10:54.741 --> 10:56.090
and I have to make sure

10:56.177 --> 10:57.613
that you have enough
good food to eat,

10:57.700 --> 10:59.049
that you get a good education.

10:59.136 --> 11:01.965
- Well there's plenty
of food to be had here.

11:02.052 --> 11:04.533
And I've got my
books to learn from.

11:04.620 --> 11:07.362
- But you said you
already knew them all.

11:07.449 --> 11:08.929
Wouldn't you like
to read new books,

11:09.016 --> 11:11.540
go to a library?

11:11.627 --> 11:13.150
- To a library?

11:13.237 --> 11:15.196
- Yeah, there they have
hundreds and hundreds of books

11:15.283 --> 11:19.330
about anything you can
imagine and they're all free.

11:20.680 --> 11:21.419
- Hundreds?

11:25.293 --> 11:29.645
But what about the
homestead and the animals?

11:29.732 --> 11:31.342
I have to stay here.

11:31.429 --> 11:33.475
I have to take
care of everything.

11:33.562 --> 11:35.303
- We'll resettle
the animals for you.

11:38.828 --> 11:39.524
- I don't know.

11:41.048 --> 11:42.571
- [Callier] Brennan,
we need to head out.

11:42.658 --> 11:44.529
- Finch, it's time.

11:48.751 --> 11:49.578
Sheriff's waiting.

11:52.276 --> 11:53.190
- It's not for good.

11:54.235 --> 11:56.150
I'm coming back.

11:56.237 --> 11:56.890
- Okay.

11:59.849 --> 12:02.460
- If you did your reading last
night, the quiz will be easy.

12:02.547 --> 12:04.201
Thomas Jefferson once said

12:04.288 --> 12:06.987
nothing can stop the man with
the right mental attitude

12:07.074 --> 12:08.945
from achieving his goal.

12:09.032 --> 12:11.121
Nothing on earth can help,

12:11.208 --> 12:13.123
Toby clear your desk, please.

12:15.343 --> 12:16.257
See me after class.

12:24.308 --> 12:27.007
[bell ringing]

12:33.709 --> 12:34.492
Sit.

12:37.800 --> 12:39.323
Toby, you have not turned in

12:39.410 --> 12:41.064
your last four
homework assignments

12:41.151 --> 12:43.588
and you are now
failing this class.

12:43.675 --> 12:45.112
You're capable of passing.

12:45.199 --> 12:48.289
I've seen what you can do
when you apply yourself.

12:48.376 --> 12:51.292
Is something preventing
you from doing your work?

12:51.379 --> 12:52.162
Is there a problem at home?

12:52.249 --> 12:53.860
- No.

12:53.947 --> 12:55.426
- Look, I'm willing
to work with you,

12:55.513 --> 12:57.254
but you have to meet me halfway.

12:57.341 --> 12:59.256
I will take your back
work at a reduced grade

12:59.343 --> 13:01.258
if you get it into me by Monday.

13:01.345 --> 13:03.304
Otherwise I'll have to call
a parent teacher conference

13:03.391 --> 13:05.132
and sort this out.

13:05.219 --> 13:07.134
Can I give you another
piece of advice?

13:09.745 --> 13:12.095
Take up a sport, join a club.

13:12.182 --> 13:13.705
The other kids might
include you more

13:13.793 --> 13:15.142
if they got to know you

13:15.229 --> 13:16.317
a little bit better
outside of class.

13:16.404 --> 13:17.666
- Can I go now?

13:17.753 --> 13:19.233
- Monday, that's the deadline.

13:25.021 --> 13:26.240
[phone ringing]

13:26.327 --> 13:27.371
- His first time in a car.

13:27.458 --> 13:28.938
Won't this be fun?

13:29.025 --> 13:30.984
Hines, I need my car detailed
and get CPS down here.

13:31.071 --> 13:32.376
- [Janelle] And
get him some water

13:32.463 --> 13:34.117
and something to
settle with stomach.

13:36.511 --> 13:38.339
- What is this place?

13:38.426 --> 13:40.167
- [Callier] Has
anybody seen Janie?

13:40.254 --> 13:41.821
- [Janelle] Finch.

13:43.997 --> 13:45.912
- Janie, where's my case
file from yesterday?

13:45.999 --> 13:46.782
- I'm on it.

14:02.189 --> 14:03.407
- Extension 401, please.

14:04.408 --> 14:05.627
This is Janelle Brennan.

14:07.803 --> 14:08.717
Yes, I'll hold.

14:17.030 --> 14:18.640
Finch.

14:18.727 --> 14:22.949
Jeff, you got him flaming hot
chips to settle his stomach?

14:23.036 --> 14:24.211
- It helps me.

14:25.995 --> 14:26.953
- Hey, sorry I'm late.

14:27.040 --> 14:28.998
- Steve, I'm glad to see you.

14:29.085 --> 14:30.565
Finch, this is Steve Anderson

14:30.652 --> 14:32.088
with Child Protective Services.

14:32.175 --> 14:33.655
- Child Protective?

14:33.742 --> 14:35.048
- It's an agency designed
to help young people

14:35.135 --> 14:36.092
in your situation.

14:36.179 --> 14:37.659
- My situation?

14:37.746 --> 14:39.139
- Yeah, you and I are
gonna go to my office,

14:39.226 --> 14:40.749
I'm gonna get some
information from you.

14:40.836 --> 14:42.185
Then we'll have a
doctor check you out

14:42.272 --> 14:43.708
and get you assigned
to a foster family.

14:43.795 --> 14:45.145
- Foster family?

14:45.232 --> 14:46.886
- Steve, this is all
very new to Finch.

14:46.973 --> 14:49.671
You may need to go slowly
and explain things in detail.

14:49.758 --> 14:50.541
- Of course.

14:50.628 --> 14:51.716
This is Paul Kramer.

14:51.803 --> 14:53.022
He's one of our foster parents.

14:53.109 --> 14:54.154
I need to take this.

14:55.764 --> 14:56.547
- Foster parents?

14:58.071 --> 14:59.681
- You'll need to be
placed in a temporary home

14:59.768 --> 15:01.813
with a family who
will look after you.

15:01.901 --> 15:04.077
- But you said that you
were responsible for me.

15:06.253 --> 15:08.081
- I didn't mean me personally.

15:08.168 --> 15:09.517
- But that's what you said.

15:09.604 --> 15:10.692
- Finch, it'll be all right.

15:10.779 --> 15:11.823
I know Paul Kramer.

15:11.911 --> 15:13.303
He has a wonderful family

15:13.390 --> 15:15.305
who will make sure you
have everything you need.

15:15.392 --> 15:16.437
- No, no, no, I
want to go back now.

15:16.524 --> 15:17.873
- Whoa, easy, easy.

15:17.960 --> 15:18.656
- I just need to go home.

15:18.743 --> 15:20.180
- Finch stop.

15:20.267 --> 15:21.137
- [Male] No one's gonna
hurt you, just calm down.

15:21.224 --> 15:22.095
- [Janelle] Leave him alone.

15:22.182 --> 15:24.227
- I really need to go home.

15:24.314 --> 15:26.099
- Call psych, we're
bringing him in right now.

15:26.186 --> 15:28.057
- He doesn't understand
what you're doing.

15:28.144 --> 15:29.624
- [Finch] Let go of me.

15:29.711 --> 15:31.713
- Just explain it to him, Steve.

15:37.284 --> 15:39.851
Hey, sorry I'm late, crazy day.

15:39.939 --> 15:40.765
- Welcome home.

15:41.723 --> 15:44.160
[gentle music]

15:47.468 --> 15:50.253
- Lisa, the school called to
say you failed every class

15:50.340 --> 15:52.473
and you're gonna have to
repeat the sixth grade.

15:52.560 --> 15:53.474
- Okay.

15:53.561 --> 15:55.519
- Jack, NASA called.

15:55.606 --> 15:57.304
They definitely want you
for the Mars mission.

15:57.391 --> 15:58.653
You leave in the morning.

16:00.176 --> 16:01.699
- Mom, you're home.

16:01.786 --> 16:03.049
- Oh, hi mom.

16:03.136 --> 16:03.832
- There are my babies.

16:03.919 --> 16:05.399
Devices down.

16:07.096 --> 16:09.316
So let's hear it.

16:09.403 --> 16:10.186
How was school?

16:11.753 --> 16:13.407
- The teacher called Heath
and me up to the board

16:13.494 --> 16:15.235
to solve a quadratic equation.

16:15.322 --> 16:17.106
- What's a quadratic equation?

16:17.193 --> 16:21.589
- It's a complicated
math problem.

16:21.676 --> 16:23.025
And?

16:23.112 --> 16:24.722
- Heath gives me
this yeah right look

16:24.809 --> 16:27.290
'cause he thinks he's the
smartest guy in the class.

16:27.377 --> 16:28.117
- And?

16:28.204 --> 16:29.814
- Nailed it.

16:29.901 --> 16:32.208
Heath had to get help from
the teacher to finish it.

16:32.295 --> 16:34.036
- Up top, yes.

16:34.123 --> 16:35.733
- Where's Toby?

16:35.820 --> 16:39.476
- He lost track of
time over at Drake's.

16:39.563 --> 16:41.087
He's on his way home now.

16:41.174 --> 16:42.436
- [Janelle] Well,
this looks wonderful.

16:42.523 --> 16:44.046
I am starving.

16:44.133 --> 16:48.224
- Did you find what
you were looking for?

16:48.311 --> 16:51.097
- Yeah, we found him.

16:51.184 --> 16:53.316
- Dad finished chapter
21 of his book today.

16:53.403 --> 16:54.143
- He did?

16:54.230 --> 16:55.623
That's wonderful.

16:55.710 --> 16:57.625
- Yep, I have one
more chapter to finish

16:57.712 --> 16:59.670
before the manuscript
deadline on Monday.

16:59.757 --> 17:01.281
- We have to keep the
house quiet this weekend

17:01.368 --> 17:02.760
so dad can write.

17:02.847 --> 17:04.893
I volunteered to
go stay at Dina's.

17:04.980 --> 17:06.460
- Oh, that's quite
the sacrifice.

17:06.547 --> 17:09.071
- It's vital to
support the arts.

17:09.158 --> 17:11.030
- And I said that if
Toby makes me mad,

17:11.117 --> 17:13.989
I'll scream into my
pillow so I won't bug dad.

17:14.076 --> 17:16.035
- I like the way
you're planning ahead.

17:20.648 --> 17:22.084
- You're almost an hour late.

17:22.171 --> 17:23.172
- Sorry.

17:24.739 --> 17:25.827
- How was your day at school?

17:25.914 --> 17:26.741
- Fine.

17:26.828 --> 17:28.047
- Oh, I almost forgot,

17:28.134 --> 17:30.353
I got an A on my
science report on frogs.

17:30.440 --> 17:32.703
- Hey, congratulations, champ.

17:32.790 --> 17:34.183
Toby, you never told me

17:34.270 --> 17:36.229
how you did on your
math test last week.

17:36.316 --> 17:37.926
- You never asked.

17:41.799 --> 17:44.976
- So Deputy Brennan,
AKA supermom,

17:45.064 --> 17:49.198
found a lost boy up in the
mountains today and rescued him.

17:49.285 --> 17:50.417
- I don't know about rescuing

17:50.504 --> 17:52.636
but yes, we brought down a boy

17:52.723 --> 17:53.942
who'd been living
up in the mountains.

17:54.029 --> 17:55.030
- Like Mowgli?

17:55.117 --> 17:56.597
Was he raised by wolves?

17:56.684 --> 17:57.989
- Seriously?

17:58.077 --> 18:00.253
- No, Jack, he had
a human family.

18:00.340 --> 18:02.603
- Was he wild and
grungy looking?

18:02.690 --> 18:05.997
- No, there was
nothing wild about him.

18:06.085 --> 18:07.042
- He's probably dumb as a rock

18:07.129 --> 18:08.435
if he's never been in school.

18:08.522 --> 18:10.959
- He's a normal boy
just like everyone else.

18:11.046 --> 18:12.569
- No one's saying-

18:12.656 --> 18:15.311
- He's a bright caring young
man with human feelings.

18:15.398 --> 18:17.487
I don't know why
everyone has to judge him

18:17.574 --> 18:18.923
because he's different.

18:21.709 --> 18:24.103
- Fine, we get it.

18:24.190 --> 18:25.104
- Sorry mom.

18:27.018 --> 18:28.194
- No, I'm sorry.

18:28.281 --> 18:29.760
I just-

18:29.847 --> 18:31.153
- So what kinds of things
does he like to do?

18:31.240 --> 18:33.460
- Yeah, does he hunt bears?

18:33.547 --> 18:35.026
- I don't know.

18:35.114 --> 18:38.160
He raises sheep and pigs.

18:38.247 --> 18:39.248
He likes to go fishing.

18:39.335 --> 18:42.121
But mostly he loves to read.

18:42.208 --> 18:44.166
- Sounds fun.

18:44.253 --> 18:46.212
- I don't know, that
sounds pretty good to me.

18:46.299 --> 18:47.822
Sounds like my kind of kid.

18:57.397 --> 19:00.182
- Brennan, I need you to
report on the Fitch boy ASAP.

19:00.269 --> 19:03.142
CPS wants the file in
front of the judge today.

19:03.229 --> 19:04.534
- Can we move Finch
out of cell four?

19:04.621 --> 19:06.014
I've got a perp coming in.

19:06.101 --> 19:07.276
- What do you mean cell four?

19:10.149 --> 19:11.541
- I'll be in my office.

19:15.371 --> 19:16.720
Before you start,

19:16.807 --> 19:18.200
the kid had to sleep in
a jail cell last night

19:18.287 --> 19:20.376
because I didn't have any
place else to put him.

19:20.463 --> 19:21.247
- What about the Kramer's?

19:21.334 --> 19:22.770
- Couldn't take him.

19:22.857 --> 19:23.684
They said they couldn't
handle his special needs.

19:23.771 --> 19:24.598
- So you put him in jail?

19:24.685 --> 19:26.121
- For his own safety.

19:26.208 --> 19:28.428
We did everything we could
to make him comfortable.

19:28.515 --> 19:30.995
- Don't worry, CPS has already
found foster placement,

19:31.082 --> 19:32.083
he's going there tonight.

19:32.171 --> 19:33.128
- I should hope so.

19:33.215 --> 19:33.868
Who's taking him?

19:35.261 --> 19:36.914
- He's going to
the Bartlow house.

19:37.001 --> 19:38.394
- That can't be right.

19:38.481 --> 19:40.135
The Bartlow house is shut down.

19:40.222 --> 19:42.050
I busted him for
possession two weeks ago.

19:42.137 --> 19:44.095
- Nope, he got out
on a technicality.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.272
- You're gonna send
the boy to Bartlow?

19:46.359 --> 19:48.622
What was Charles
Manson's house full?

19:48.709 --> 19:49.623
- It's CPS' call.

19:49.710 --> 19:51.015
I don't have a choice.

19:51.102 --> 19:51.929
- Bartlow is not a
real foster home.

19:52.016 --> 19:53.322
It's a drug cartel.

19:53.409 --> 19:55.106
He uses those kids
to make his runs.

19:55.194 --> 19:56.978
- We don't have a say in this.

19:57.065 --> 19:58.197
- Maybe you don't, but I do.

19:58.284 --> 19:59.676
- Brennan.

19:59.763 --> 20:01.330
- No, you have seen
him Bob, he's lost.

20:01.417 --> 20:03.506
He wouldn't last one
night at Bartlow's.

20:03.593 --> 20:04.899
- [Callier] Janelle.

20:04.986 --> 20:05.639
- Hines, forward
my calls, will you?

20:05.726 --> 20:07.075
- Sure thing.

20:07.162 --> 20:08.207
- [Janelle] I'll be
at the courthouse.

20:08.294 --> 20:09.077
- Hines!

20:13.037 --> 20:13.995
- I'm sorry, lieutenant,

20:14.082 --> 20:15.170
Judge Raymond is in court today.

20:15.257 --> 20:16.040
Can I make you an appointment?

20:16.127 --> 20:17.041
- This is urgent.

20:17.128 --> 20:19.000
I can't make it, Marguerite.

20:20.175 --> 20:22.525
Marguerite, am I
glad to see you.

20:22.612 --> 20:23.570
- Janelle, how are you?

20:23.657 --> 20:24.919
- Do you have the CPS case

20:25.006 --> 20:27.095
for the Finch boy
from Briar Rock?

20:27.182 --> 20:29.750
- No, Jason in the state office
is handling that one, why?

20:29.837 --> 20:31.317
- Can you get it?

20:31.404 --> 20:33.710
They placed the boy at
Ernest Barlow's house.

20:33.797 --> 20:35.277
- I thought Bartlow was in jail.

20:35.364 --> 20:38.541
- Exactly, he has got
to go someplace else.

20:38.628 --> 20:41.283
- Even if I could get
the case reassigned,

20:41.370 --> 20:44.286
once he's placed, I can't
remove him without cause.

20:44.373 --> 20:45.461
- Cause?

20:45.548 --> 20:47.115
You know what Bartlow is.

20:47.202 --> 20:48.899
- He's never been convicted.

20:48.986 --> 20:51.511
Besides there's no place
else for the boy to go.

20:51.598 --> 20:52.338
- I'll take him.

20:52.425 --> 20:54.078
Place him with me.

20:54.165 --> 20:56.907
- Janelle, you have to be
certified for foster care.

20:56.994 --> 20:58.257
- I am.

20:58.344 --> 20:59.867
We are, Keith and
I are certified.

20:59.954 --> 21:01.390
We had to be before
we adopted Jackson.

21:01.477 --> 21:03.392
I could have the paperwork
to you within the hour.

21:03.479 --> 21:04.915
- I'm sorry.

21:05.002 --> 21:06.961
I don't like Bartlow
any more than you do,

21:07.048 --> 21:09.006
but rules are rules.

21:09.093 --> 21:10.443
And right now neither one of us

21:10.530 --> 21:12.575
has the authority
to move the boy.

21:12.662 --> 21:14.838
So if you'll,
excuse me, I'm late.

21:16.144 --> 21:16.884
- Adoption.

21:18.581 --> 21:19.147
- What?

21:20.191 --> 21:21.541
- If Finch was being adopted,

21:21.628 --> 21:23.456
he could be pulled
from Bartlow's.

21:23.543 --> 21:25.414
- That's true, but-

21:25.501 --> 21:27.895
- Okay, so we're adopting him.

21:27.982 --> 21:29.418
- Janelle-

21:29.505 --> 21:31.072
- You could transfer him
to us right away today.

21:31.159 --> 21:34.641
- You can't just pretend
to want to adopt.

21:34.728 --> 21:38.122
- It'll buy him some time until
I can find him a safer home.

21:38.209 --> 21:40.037
- What am I supposed
to tell the judge,

21:40.124 --> 21:41.822
or the boy for that matter?

21:41.909 --> 21:43.998
- That Keith and I
are giving him a home.

21:44.085 --> 21:45.739
- For how long?

21:45.826 --> 21:47.262
Keith doesn't even know

21:47.349 --> 21:49.046
that we're having this
conversation, does he?

21:49.133 --> 21:50.657
- For however long it takes.

21:50.744 --> 21:52.223
I promise you, Marguerite.

21:52.311 --> 21:54.617
I will not dump Finch
back into the system.

21:54.704 --> 21:57.446
I will take care of him until
a permanent home can be found.

21:58.926 --> 22:00.362
- I hope you know
what you're doing.

22:00.449 --> 22:02.103
- So you'll talk to Judge
Raymond this afternoon?

22:02.190 --> 22:03.539
- I'll see what I can do,

22:03.626 --> 22:05.802
but I'm not making any promises.

22:05.889 --> 22:08.370
- Please, make it
happen, Marguerite.

22:20.382 --> 22:22.166
- I don't know how
you pulled this off.

22:22.253 --> 22:23.907
- Don't ask.

22:23.994 --> 22:25.735
Hey, can we talk?

22:25.822 --> 22:27.171
- We'll leave you to it.

22:30.131 --> 22:31.480
- Look, Finch-

22:31.567 --> 22:32.699
- I want to go home.

22:34.222 --> 22:36.572
- I'm afraid that's
not possible.

22:36.659 --> 22:38.705
- Are you gonna
lock me up again?

22:38.792 --> 22:40.141
Because if you don't,

22:40.228 --> 22:42.099
I'm going to find a way
back to that mountain.

22:42.186 --> 22:46.016
- Okay, okay, yeah,
I'll take you back.

22:46.103 --> 22:47.975
But before we go,

22:48.062 --> 22:50.020
I'd like you to come
to my house for dinner

22:50.107 --> 22:51.239
and meet my family.

22:53.110 --> 22:54.460
- Your family?

22:54.547 --> 22:57.593
- Yeah, my husband
and my three kids.

22:57.680 --> 23:00.117
I have a son who's
just your age.

23:00.204 --> 23:01.292
I'd like you to meet them.

23:02.598 --> 23:03.817
Will you do that for me?

23:05.862 --> 23:07.037
- And then we'll go back?

23:09.910 --> 23:11.694
- If that's what you want, yes.

23:17.570 --> 23:20.181
- Will we ride in the car again?

23:20.268 --> 23:21.748
- No, I completely understand.

23:21.835 --> 23:22.966
- Hi dad.

23:23.053 --> 23:25.578
- Shh, he's on the phone.

23:25.665 --> 23:26.927
- I'm gonna go say
hello to Lenny.

23:27.014 --> 23:28.276
- Rats don't talk.

23:28.363 --> 23:29.973
- He's not a rat,
he's a hamster.

23:30.060 --> 23:31.975
- Oh, well in that case.

23:32.062 --> 23:33.586
- Well, I appreciate
you calling.

23:34.935 --> 23:36.415
- This smells delicious.

23:37.546 --> 23:39.026
I'm starving.

23:39.113 --> 23:40.462
- I thought you were staying
at Dina's this weekend.

23:40.549 --> 23:42.203
- Her brother decided
to come home from school

23:42.290 --> 23:44.466
so they're having some
family time together.

23:45.511 --> 23:46.990
I'm going to my room.

23:53.519 --> 23:55.259
- That was your history teacher,

23:55.346 --> 23:57.000
Miss Barnett on the phone.

23:57.958 --> 23:58.654
- Oh?

24:01.396 --> 24:03.050
- Anything you want to tell me?

24:06.053 --> 24:07.054
- Dinner smells good.

24:09.056 --> 24:10.753
- Well, what do
you want me to say?

24:10.840 --> 24:12.189
I'm sorry?

24:12.276 --> 24:14.017
I'm sorry I don't get
straight A's like Lisa.

24:14.104 --> 24:15.628
- Nobody expects that.

24:15.715 --> 24:17.891
- Yeah, because
I'm your dumb kid.

24:17.978 --> 24:19.240
- Oh, come on Toby.

24:19.327 --> 24:20.589
You know that's
not what I meant.

24:20.676 --> 24:22.112
- I'll be up in my room.

24:22.199 --> 24:23.592
- And then we'll sit
down with your mother

24:23.679 --> 24:25.333
and talk about this
after dinner tonight.

24:25.420 --> 24:27.509
- You have a publishing
deadline, remember?

24:28.379 --> 24:30.120
- We'll talk.

24:30.207 --> 24:30.991
- Sure we will.

24:35.865 --> 24:38.651
- Lenny's gone, I can't
find him anywhere.

24:38.738 --> 24:40.827
- Did you close his cage after
you fed him this morning?

24:40.914 --> 24:41.871
- I thought I did.

24:41.958 --> 24:43.046
We have to find him.

24:56.277 --> 24:57.931
- You live here?

24:58.018 --> 24:58.801
- Yeah.

25:02.413 --> 25:03.240
- It's really big.

25:04.807 --> 25:07.767
It's like having the
outside on the inside.

25:10.596 --> 25:11.379
- Hmm.

25:13.250 --> 25:15.252
I've never thought of
it that way before.

25:17.124 --> 25:19.126
You can put your stuff
down right over there.

25:19.213 --> 25:21.171
Let me go find everyone
and I'll introduce you.

25:24.827 --> 25:27.700
[mysterious music]

25:58.426 --> 26:00.080
- I don't see him anywhere.

26:00.167 --> 26:02.125
- Hey, what's going on?

26:02.212 --> 26:03.649
- Lenny got out again.

26:03.736 --> 26:04.998
- Oh.

26:05.085 --> 26:07.087
- [Lisa] That rat
better not come near me.

26:07.174 --> 26:08.958
- He's not a rat.

26:09.045 --> 26:10.612
- Take Sebastian outside please

26:10.699 --> 26:12.614
and go finish the salad.

26:12.701 --> 26:13.963
Thank you.

26:14.050 --> 26:15.138
- Have your checked your closet?

26:15.225 --> 26:16.705
He likes to get in your shoes.

26:16.792 --> 26:18.185
- No.

26:18.272 --> 26:21.144
[mysterious music]

26:53.220 --> 26:55.570
[screaming]

26:55.657 --> 26:57.224
- It attacked me.

26:57.311 --> 26:58.094
- I got it.

27:01.054 --> 27:01.968
- No!

27:02.055 --> 27:05.058
- You leave my hamster alone.

27:05.145 --> 27:08.061
- Jack, take Lenny and put
him back up in his cage.

27:08.148 --> 27:09.671
- Cage?

27:09.758 --> 27:12.848
You know you really should
try raising rabbits.

27:12.935 --> 27:15.068
That thing's hardly a mouthful.

27:15.155 --> 27:16.722
- Ugh.

27:16.809 --> 27:18.680
- No, hamsters, aren't
for eating, they're pets.

27:18.767 --> 27:20.160
- Who is this guy?

27:20.247 --> 27:22.292
- Oh, I'm sorry.

27:22.379 --> 27:25.426
Everyone, this is Finch.

27:25.513 --> 27:28.342
I invited him to stay
with us for dinner.

27:28.429 --> 27:30.823
- I'm Keith, hi.

27:30.910 --> 27:32.520
So how do you two
know each other?

27:32.607 --> 27:35.479
- Finch is the young man I met
up on Briar Rock yesterday.

27:35.566 --> 27:37.090
- This is the
hillbilly you rescued?

27:37.177 --> 27:38.178
Ow!

27:38.265 --> 27:40.049
- Finch, these are our children,

27:40.136 --> 27:41.660
Lisa, Toby and Jack.

27:41.747 --> 27:43.052
You've met Lenny.

27:43.139 --> 27:43.923
- Dinner, huh?

27:44.010 --> 27:44.967
What's he gonna eat?

27:45.054 --> 27:46.055
- We'll go put Lenny away.

27:46.142 --> 27:47.840
- And we'll finish up in here.

27:47.927 --> 27:49.493
Toby and Lisa, set
the table please.

27:49.580 --> 27:52.235
And Finch, why don't
you go wash up?

27:58.111 --> 27:59.460
- Why is he here?

27:59.547 --> 28:01.505
- Because I invited him.

28:01.592 --> 28:05.509
So be polite and please do not
use the word hillbilly again.

28:05.596 --> 28:06.293
- Fine.

28:06.380 --> 28:07.860
How about Yokel?

28:07.947 --> 28:09.165
- Toby.

28:09.252 --> 28:12.125
- Where did he
get those clothes?

28:12.212 --> 28:14.127
- I imagine they're homemade.

28:14.214 --> 28:15.911
That's how they do
things where he's from.

28:15.998 --> 28:17.130
- That's not all they do.

28:17.217 --> 28:18.000
Look.

28:19.175 --> 28:20.002
- Oh no.

28:20.089 --> 28:21.961
[Playful Music]

28:22.048 --> 28:24.267
- He's a total nut job.

28:24.354 --> 28:26.748
- Look, it's only for
a couple of hours.

28:26.835 --> 28:29.098
So let's try and make
him feel at home.

28:29.185 --> 28:32.014
- Dina is not going
to believe this.

28:38.499 --> 28:39.892
- This all looks wonderful.

28:39.979 --> 28:41.632
- Yeah, I'm starving.

28:48.378 --> 28:49.728
- What?

28:49.815 --> 28:52.905
- Finch, would you like
to say grace for us?

28:57.039 --> 28:58.127
- Thank you God

28:58.214 --> 29:00.651
for your bountiful provision

29:00.739 --> 29:03.306
and for letting me spend
time with this nice family.

29:04.568 --> 29:05.526
Amen.

29:05.613 --> 29:06.396
- [All] Amen.

29:08.137 --> 29:10.139
- Finch, I hope
you like spaghetti.

29:10.226 --> 29:12.228
- I don't believe
I've met her, ma'am.

29:12.315 --> 29:14.143
[laughing]

29:14.230 --> 29:15.536
- Guests first.

29:15.623 --> 29:18.931
Finch, spaghetti isn't a person.

29:19.018 --> 29:20.106
It's the name of this food.

29:20.193 --> 29:21.498
- Oh

29:21.585 --> 29:23.283
- It comes from a
country known as Italy.

29:23.370 --> 29:26.155
- Actually, it originated
as Chinese noodles.

29:26.242 --> 29:28.157
Marco Polo introduced
it to the Italians

29:28.244 --> 29:29.724
when he returned from China.

29:29.811 --> 29:32.074
- I don't know if I
like Chinese noodles.

29:32.161 --> 29:33.119
- Don't be an idiot.

29:33.206 --> 29:34.207
- Toby, that's enough.

29:36.296 --> 29:39.386
So Finch, Janelle tells me
that you're an avid reader.

29:39.473 --> 29:40.779
- Yes, sir.

29:40.866 --> 29:42.519
- Well, what's
your favorite book?

29:42.606 --> 29:43.956
- "Oliver Twist".

29:44.043 --> 29:47.046
- Dickens, he is my
favorite as well.

29:47.133 --> 29:48.787
Have you ever read
"David Copperfield"?

29:48.874 --> 29:50.353
- No sir.

29:50.440 --> 29:52.791
- After dinner tonight,
I'll take you to the library

29:52.878 --> 29:56.490
and you can see my 1917
illustrated edition.

29:56.577 --> 29:57.970
The artwork is stunning.

29:58.057 --> 29:59.885
- You have a library?

29:59.972 --> 30:01.364
- I do.

30:01.451 --> 30:03.976
After dinner, we'll
take you on a tour.

30:04.063 --> 30:06.021
- Oh, speaking of books,

30:06.108 --> 30:08.154
how did your meeting
with the editor go?

30:08.241 --> 30:12.114
- Oh, he said as long as I
make my deadline this weekend,

30:12.201 --> 30:13.986
we're good to go for
a November release

30:14.073 --> 30:16.075
right before the
Christmas shopping season.

30:16.162 --> 30:18.164
[Slurps Loudly]

30:22.429 --> 30:24.344
- How do you like
spaghetti, Finch?

30:24.431 --> 30:25.258
- Nice.

30:26.650 --> 30:28.739
- Did I do something wrong?

30:31.090 --> 30:32.308
- No.

30:34.441 --> 30:35.224
No.

30:38.227 --> 30:39.707
When in Rome.

30:39.794 --> 30:42.014
[laughing]

30:49.108 --> 30:51.240
- It tastes better this way.

30:51.327 --> 30:52.502
- Come on, Toby.

30:52.589 --> 30:54.940
- Toby, it's easy.

31:04.079 --> 31:05.254
I got some in my beard.

31:07.256 --> 31:09.084
I'll save it for later.

31:09.171 --> 31:11.173
[laughing]

31:12.958 --> 31:14.046
- They've finally snapped.

31:25.187 --> 31:26.667
- That kid is amazing.

31:26.754 --> 31:28.147
He took one look at the library

31:28.234 --> 31:29.888
and he got that expression

31:29.975 --> 31:32.064
that Jack gets when we
go to the pet store.

31:32.151 --> 31:35.023
- There are more books in there
than he ever knew existed.

31:35.110 --> 31:36.372
- He picked up my "Walden"

31:36.459 --> 31:38.200
and started quoting
Thoreau to me.

31:38.287 --> 31:40.333
What teenager today can do that?

31:40.420 --> 31:41.769
- [Janelle] Where is he now?

31:41.856 --> 31:43.945
- Jack took him out
to the tree house.

31:44.032 --> 31:46.817
- Listen, I have something
to tell you all about Finch.

31:46.905 --> 31:50.212
CPS took him in, but
he has no place to go.

31:50.299 --> 31:52.432
Last night, he slept in a
jail cell at the station

31:52.519 --> 31:54.086
because they couldn't
place him anywhere.

31:54.173 --> 31:57.916
Today, they were gonna place
him with a known drug felon.

31:58.003 --> 31:59.787
To stop that from happening,

31:59.874 --> 32:01.789
I told them that we
were adopting him.

32:02.877 --> 32:03.573
- What?

32:03.660 --> 32:04.400
- He's staying?

32:04.487 --> 32:05.445
- Not with us?

32:05.532 --> 32:07.012
- We're not really adopting him.

32:07.099 --> 32:09.405
It's just a cover until I
can find him a safe family

32:09.492 --> 32:10.711
that will take him permanently.

32:10.798 --> 32:11.755
- How could you decide this

32:11.842 --> 32:13.279
without talking to me first?

32:13.366 --> 32:16.021
- There was no time
and he was in danger.

32:16.108 --> 32:17.283
- I don't want him here.

32:17.370 --> 32:18.327
- He's so weird.

32:18.414 --> 32:20.025
He wanted to eat Lenny.

32:20.112 --> 32:21.896
- He needs our help.

32:21.983 --> 32:23.158
And it's just for
a little while.

32:23.245 --> 32:24.855
- I don't believe this.

32:24.943 --> 32:26.248
- At least with Jackson,

32:26.335 --> 32:28.033
you asked us before
we adopted him.

32:30.687 --> 32:31.950
- Keith, I'm sorry.

32:32.037 --> 32:33.299
- What were you
thinking, Janelle?

32:33.386 --> 32:34.778
- He needs my help.

32:34.865 --> 32:36.867
- Sometimes I need
your help too.

32:38.608 --> 32:41.350
[gentle music]

32:41.437 --> 32:44.875
You know how important
this deadline is to me.

32:44.963 --> 32:48.879
You know how important
becoming a writer is to me.

32:48.967 --> 32:51.273
I gave up a 15 year job
at the investment firm

32:51.360 --> 32:52.057
to try for this.

32:52.144 --> 32:53.623
- I know.

32:53.710 --> 32:56.322
- This weekend was
supposed to be about that.

32:56.409 --> 32:58.280
How am I supposed
to finish my book

32:58.367 --> 32:59.847
when I have to waste all my time

32:59.934 --> 33:02.110
taking care of some
backwards orphan

33:02.197 --> 33:04.634
who doesn't know a faucet
from an electric socket?

33:04.721 --> 33:06.201
I will take care of him.

33:06.288 --> 33:08.943
I promise you, you won't
even know we're here.

33:09.030 --> 33:10.292
I'll talk to the kids

33:10.379 --> 33:13.034
and we'll keep the
house quiet all weekend

33:13.121 --> 33:15.950
and Monday, I'll find
a family to take Finch.

33:16.037 --> 33:16.559
- [Jackson] Mom.

33:18.083 --> 33:20.302
- Honey, how long have
you been standing there?

33:20.389 --> 33:22.391
- Not long, we came in
and get my walkie talkies

33:22.478 --> 33:24.045
to take to the tree house.

33:24.132 --> 33:25.177
- We?

33:25.264 --> 33:27.396
- Finch was here
too but he left.

33:27.483 --> 33:29.050
- You suppose he heard us?

33:29.137 --> 33:30.225
- Oh, he heard you.

33:31.226 --> 33:32.227
- I'd better go find him.

33:32.314 --> 33:33.576
- No, let me do it.

33:33.663 --> 33:35.013
- No, you go write.

33:35.100 --> 33:36.492
He's my responsibility.

33:36.579 --> 33:39.017
- No, I shouldn't
have said what I said.

33:39.104 --> 33:40.018
I'll talk to him.

33:42.368 --> 33:45.240
- Mom, are you and
dad mad at each other?

33:45.327 --> 33:47.025
- No, honey.

33:47.112 --> 33:49.027
We just had a
little disagreement.

33:49.114 --> 33:50.332
- About Finch?

33:50.419 --> 33:51.246
- Yeah.

33:51.333 --> 33:52.073
- I like him.

33:53.205 --> 33:54.423
- Yeah, me too.

34:04.129 --> 34:06.000
- [Keith] Finch, wait up.

34:06.087 --> 34:08.220
- You don't need to concern
yourself with me, Mr. Brennan.

34:08.307 --> 34:11.136
- Look Finch, about
what I said back there.

34:11.223 --> 34:14.052
- I just came over for
dinner because I was invited.

34:14.139 --> 34:15.966
I'm going home.

34:16.054 --> 34:17.533
- Briar Rock is a
long way from here.

34:17.620 --> 34:18.360
- I'll get there.

34:19.579 --> 34:21.015
- You know when you're hunting

34:21.102 --> 34:24.279
and you get focused
on the deer or rabbit

34:24.366 --> 34:26.281
and you don't see anything else?

34:26.368 --> 34:30.111
The woods around you
disappear, all sound stops,

34:30.198 --> 34:32.331
all you hear is your heartbeat,

34:32.418 --> 34:34.985
all you see is the slightest
movement of the prey?

34:38.685 --> 34:39.338
- Yeah.

34:41.079 --> 34:45.866
- That's how it is for my
brain right now about my book.

34:45.953 --> 34:47.955
I wasn't thinking
about anyone else.

34:49.696 --> 34:52.133
I didn't mean any
of those dumb things

34:52.220 --> 34:53.830
that I said back there.

34:53.917 --> 34:55.963
- I can take care of myself,

34:56.050 --> 34:57.660
but no one listens to me.

34:57.747 --> 35:00.010
- I believe that you can
take care of yourself,

35:00.098 --> 35:00.968
but you don't have to.

35:02.448 --> 35:04.754
It's too late to go
anywhere tonight.

35:04.841 --> 35:06.365
Come on back to
the house with me.

35:08.802 --> 35:09.759
- And stay with you?

35:11.109 --> 35:11.761
- Not permanently.

35:13.198 --> 35:16.114
Just until you know what
you want to do next.

35:16.201 --> 35:19.204
Hey, you can read "David
Copperfield" while you're there.

35:21.075 --> 35:22.468
What do you say, Finch?

35:22.555 --> 35:23.773
Just for a little while.

35:26.863 --> 35:28.474
- Did God tell you
to come after me

35:30.040 --> 35:33.522
or did you just decide
that on your own?

35:33.609 --> 35:35.133
- I'm not sure what you mean.

35:37.135 --> 35:39.528
- Whenever my gram had
a big decision to make,

35:39.615 --> 35:42.662
she would stop for a minute

35:42.749 --> 35:45.055
and she would get
real still and quiet

35:45.143 --> 35:47.928
and I knew that she was
praying to God in her head

35:48.015 --> 35:50.017
asking him what to do.

35:51.540 --> 35:55.065
And then she would get
this big smile on her face

35:55.153 --> 35:57.372
and she would have her answer.

35:59.505 --> 36:01.202
- It worked that
fast every time?

36:01.289 --> 36:04.031
- She said that because
she's a simple lady

36:04.118 --> 36:06.686
God usually kept the
answers pretty simple too.

36:08.209 --> 36:12.953
He often said yes
and no or we'll see.

36:14.520 --> 36:16.348
That's how she kept
on the right path.

36:18.872 --> 36:20.917
Is that how you do
it, Mr. Brennan?

36:22.397 --> 36:23.746
- Yeah, I guess.

36:25.226 --> 36:29.230
If I'm honest, I
usually jump in first

36:29.317 --> 36:31.101
and then ask God for
a bail out later.

36:33.365 --> 36:34.844
- That's not how I
do it, Mr. Brennan.

36:36.411 --> 36:39.458
- All right, let's do
it your gran's way.

36:41.111 --> 36:43.201
On the count of three,
we'll ask together.

36:44.114 --> 36:47.292
One, two, three.

36:58.216 --> 36:58.999
We'll see?

37:01.610 --> 37:02.350
- We'll see.

37:04.657 --> 37:05.745
- [Keith] Okay then.

37:05.832 --> 37:07.268
You know you should write down

37:07.355 --> 37:08.922
some of your memories
of your gran and pap.

37:09.009 --> 37:11.141
I'll bet you have some
interesting tales to tell.

37:11.229 --> 37:12.969
- [Finch] My gran once
took down a cougar

37:13.056 --> 37:13.970
with her knitting needles.

37:14.057 --> 37:15.798
- [Keith] That's what I thought.

37:17.931 --> 37:19.672
[knocking]

37:19.759 --> 37:22.501
- [Janelle] Toby, can I come in?

37:22.588 --> 37:23.328
- I'm really busy.

37:24.285 --> 37:25.765
I've got homework to do.

37:25.852 --> 37:27.419
[soft piano music]

37:27.506 --> 37:31.205
- Toby, I'm sorry the
way this all came out.

37:31.292 --> 37:32.946
I didn't mean to
spring this on you.

37:33.033 --> 37:34.426
- Where's dad?

37:34.513 --> 37:35.992
- He went to go find Finch.

37:36.906 --> 37:37.690
- Figures.

37:39.779 --> 37:41.868
- I think it would be
better if we talked.

37:43.522 --> 37:45.088
- There's nothing to talk about.

37:45.175 --> 37:47.743
- If you would
just open the door.

37:47.830 --> 37:48.527
- Goodnight, mom.

37:49.484 --> 37:51.486
- [Janelle] Toby please.

37:51.573 --> 37:52.487
- Goodnight.

37:57.536 --> 37:58.276
[gentle music]

38:54.723 --> 38:57.378
[dramatic music]

39:35.721 --> 39:36.548
- Who is it?

39:36.635 --> 39:37.766
- Miss Jessica Hague.

39:39.464 --> 39:40.552
- Yeah, what?

39:40.639 --> 39:41.944
- My name is Lane Billings.

39:42.031 --> 39:44.120
I'm with Alpha Gas Corp.

39:44.207 --> 39:47.080
- Do I look like I need
anything from a gas company?

39:47.167 --> 39:48.560
- I have some papers here

39:48.647 --> 39:51.301
that you might be
interested in reading.

39:51.389 --> 39:53.303
It could mean some
money for you.

39:53.391 --> 39:54.304
- Who do you think you are?

39:54.392 --> 39:56.002
I'm calling the police.

39:56.089 --> 39:58.918
- Oh, oh, oh no.

39:59.005 --> 40:01.616
I don't think you want the
police to come in there, do you?

40:01.703 --> 40:04.271
I mean, not with
what they would find.

40:05.664 --> 40:07.317
- You don't know
anything about me.

40:07.405 --> 40:08.710
[snaps finger]

40:12.148 --> 40:15.108
- Jessica Hague, 32
never been married,

40:15.195 --> 40:18.416
dropped out of Marsh
County High at 16.

40:18.503 --> 40:20.156
Your mother kicked
you out of your home

40:20.243 --> 40:23.029
when she discovered
you were pregnant.

40:23.116 --> 40:24.987
You bounced around from
friend's house to friend's house

40:25.074 --> 40:27.076
till you used them all up.

40:27.163 --> 40:29.035
Then you disappeared out
near Briar Rock Mountain

40:29.122 --> 40:31.341
for approximately three weeks,

40:31.429 --> 40:34.040
then resurfaced with
no job to speak of.

40:34.127 --> 40:36.521
Hmm, you've been busted
twice for possession,

40:36.608 --> 40:38.000
you like Will Ferrell comedies

40:38.087 --> 40:40.089
and your favorite
soda is Mountain Dew.

40:44.746 --> 40:46.444
Seems to me I know
you fairly well.

40:47.401 --> 40:48.489
- What do you want?

40:50.056 --> 40:52.798
- The real question
is what do you want?

40:53.755 --> 40:54.930
- What are you offering?

40:55.017 --> 40:56.758
- Security.

40:56.845 --> 40:59.108
Not to mention the
chance to see your son.

41:01.154 --> 41:02.329
- My son?

41:02.416 --> 41:03.069
- Mhmm.

41:04.070 --> 41:05.332
- You've seen my boy?

41:05.419 --> 41:06.638
- Mmhmm.

41:06.725 --> 41:07.421
- How is he?

41:07.508 --> 41:08.204
- Oh, he's fine.

41:09.815 --> 41:12.121
And you're both about
to do a lot better.

41:16.648 --> 41:19.041
[birds chirping]

41:22.262 --> 41:23.045
- Finch!

41:24.525 --> 41:26.396
Time for breakfast.

41:27.833 --> 41:29.225
- But I haven't
caught anything yet.

41:32.751 --> 41:35.841
- He's coming and he's
still wearing those clothes.

41:35.928 --> 41:37.451
- Stop worrying about it.

41:37.538 --> 41:38.583
- I'm going over to the Drake's.

41:38.670 --> 41:39.627
- I was hoping we all could-

41:39.714 --> 41:40.585
- No thanks.

41:40.672 --> 41:41.934
- What about breakfast?

41:42.021 --> 41:42.804
- I'm not hungry.

41:48.984 --> 41:50.116
- Morning, Finch.

41:50.203 --> 41:51.204
- Good morning.

41:53.206 --> 41:54.250
- Cool.

41:55.817 --> 41:56.514
- Is that?

42:00.474 --> 42:02.084
I hope you're hungry.

42:02.171 --> 42:03.869
- I am but I didn't
catch anything.

42:03.956 --> 42:05.435
- Oh, that's all right,

42:05.523 --> 42:07.568
I already went hunting
at the grocery store.

42:07.655 --> 42:08.569
- I want to go hunting.

42:08.656 --> 42:09.527
- Jackson.

42:11.224 --> 42:14.053
- Is that what you do
first thing every morning?

42:14.140 --> 42:16.098
- Mostly, sometimes I fish.

42:16.185 --> 42:17.186
- Can we go fishing?

42:17.273 --> 42:18.666
- Not today.

42:18.753 --> 42:20.102
Your father has his
writing deadlines

42:20.189 --> 42:21.800
so we're getting
out of the house.

42:21.887 --> 42:24.150
I was thinking we could go
to show Finch around town.

42:24.237 --> 42:26.152
What do you say, Finch?

42:26.239 --> 42:28.894
- Is there something
in particular you'd
like to see or do?

42:28.981 --> 42:30.286
- Can we go see a movie?

42:30.373 --> 42:31.853
- Yeah.
- A movie?

42:31.940 --> 42:32.724
- What do you say?

42:32.811 --> 42:34.203
Would you like that?

42:34.290 --> 42:36.815
- I think so, I've
never seen one before.

42:36.902 --> 42:38.294
- A movie it is then.

42:40.122 --> 42:44.474
- Mom, his clothes.

42:46.999 --> 42:48.609
- Let's do something
about it then.

42:52.700 --> 42:55.529
[gentle music]

