♪ But now brother
I've been found ♪

45:36.777 --> 45:38.953
[laughing]

45:39.040 --> 45:39.737
- Hey.

45:39.824 --> 45:41.173
- Hey.

45:41.260 --> 45:42.870
- Oh, looks like
things went well.

45:42.957 --> 45:44.524
- We have had a good day.

45:44.611 --> 45:46.308
- I should've known
you'd pull it off.

45:46.395 --> 45:47.483
Where's Toby?

45:47.570 --> 45:48.833
- Isn't he here?

45:48.920 --> 45:50.617
- No, I thought he was with you.

45:50.704 --> 45:52.750
- No, he went to
Drake's this morning

45:52.837 --> 45:54.055
but he should've
been back by now.

45:54.142 --> 45:54.839
- Huh.

45:54.926 --> 45:56.188
- I'll text Ruth.

45:59.060 --> 46:00.322
- How did the writing go?

46:00.409 --> 46:02.411
- Great Tiger,
thanks for asking.

46:02.498 --> 46:03.891
I've been at it all day.

46:03.978 --> 46:06.502
I've written about 20
pages of good stuff.

46:06.589 --> 46:07.677
I'm really happy with it.

46:07.765 --> 46:09.070
- Did you finish the book?

46:09.157 --> 46:11.029
- Not yet, but I'm really close.

46:11.116 --> 46:12.595
- I'm gonna go upstairs
and take a shower.

46:12.682 --> 46:13.988
- And I have to go feed Lenny.

46:15.120 --> 46:16.338
- What about you, Finch?

46:16.425 --> 46:17.775
Did you have a good time?

46:17.862 --> 46:18.993
- It was mighty fine.

46:19.994 --> 46:21.517
And I'm tuckered out.

46:21.604 --> 46:24.912
Right now, I think I'll go
read my book and go to bed.

46:24.999 --> 46:28.698
- Oh, Finch, I found this
empty journal in the library.

46:28.786 --> 46:30.048
Thought you might want to use it

46:30.135 --> 46:31.005
to write down some
of your memories

46:31.092 --> 46:33.138
from Briar Rock Mountain.

46:33.225 --> 46:33.965
- Thank you.

46:35.488 --> 46:37.707
I will, I'll start on it tonight

46:37.795 --> 46:39.187
right after I finish

46:39.274 --> 46:40.580
the next chapter of
"David Copperfield".

46:40.667 --> 46:43.148
- Oh, the book is on
the desk in the library.

46:45.237 --> 46:47.805
- Ruth said that Toby left
their house right after lunch.

46:47.892 --> 46:48.980
- Did she say where he went?

46:49.067 --> 46:50.546
- She thought he
was coming here.

46:50.633 --> 46:53.114
I called his phone, it
went directly to voicemail.

46:53.201 --> 46:54.899
You don't think
anything happened?

46:54.986 --> 46:58.424
- No, I'm sure
he'll be home soon.

46:58.511 --> 47:00.600
- Okay, I'll make
a few more calls

47:00.687 --> 47:01.993
and see if anyone has seen him.

47:11.263 --> 47:13.743
[gentle music]

47:48.909 --> 47:50.171
[glass clinking]

47:50.258 --> 47:52.260
[sizzling]

47:56.047 --> 47:58.049
- Did you find your book?

47:58.136 --> 48:00.138
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
what did you do?

48:00.225 --> 48:02.140
- [Finch] I knocked something
over and I touched this.

48:02.227 --> 48:03.402
- What did you touch?

48:03.489 --> 48:05.012
- Just this.
- Get up, get up.

48:06.709 --> 48:08.015
- Will it come back?

48:08.102 --> 48:10.061
- You had no business
touching this.

48:10.148 --> 48:11.540
- [Finch] I just wanted
to read your book.

48:11.627 --> 48:12.890
- And now it's gone.

48:14.239 --> 48:16.110
- I didn't mean to.
- Go.

48:16.197 --> 48:17.677
- I'm sorry.
- Go!

48:21.681 --> 48:22.769
- Finch?

48:22.856 --> 48:24.640
Keith, what was that all about?

48:24.727 --> 48:26.599
- He spilled water
all over the computer.

48:26.686 --> 48:27.643
It's fried.

48:27.730 --> 48:28.862
I lost everything.

48:28.949 --> 48:30.733
- Do you have a backup?

48:30.820 --> 48:32.257
- It has a backup drive in it.

48:32.344 --> 48:33.562
It may still work.

48:33.649 --> 48:34.607
- Call Uncle Jerry.

48:34.694 --> 48:35.738
He works in computers.

48:35.825 --> 48:37.088
- Yeah, he'll know what to do.

48:37.175 --> 48:39.394
- You call him, I'll clean up.

48:39.481 --> 48:40.569
- And where have you been?

48:40.656 --> 48:42.136
Your mother and I were worried.

48:42.223 --> 48:43.659
- I went over to Steve's.

48:43.746 --> 48:44.834
I forgot to call.

48:44.922 --> 48:45.792
Sorry.

48:45.879 --> 48:47.185
- When will you realize

48:47.272 --> 48:49.970
that sorry doesn't
magically fix everything?

48:50.057 --> 48:52.625
You should have called us
and told us where you were.

48:52.712 --> 48:54.322
- I just forgot.

48:54.409 --> 48:55.584
- Well, you won't forget this.

48:55.671 --> 48:57.282
You're grounded.

48:57.369 --> 48:59.284
One week, you're not leaving
this house except for school.

48:59.371 --> 49:01.025
Got it?

49:01.112 --> 49:02.809
- I got it.

49:17.824 --> 49:19.869
You know what this
means, don't you?

49:19.957 --> 49:21.132
- I didn't mean to.

49:21.219 --> 49:22.133
- If he loses that book,

49:22.220 --> 49:23.482
he'll be finished as a writer.

49:23.569 --> 49:25.223
- Finished?

49:25.310 --> 49:27.442
- You should have stayed on
that mountain where you belong.

49:27.529 --> 49:28.617
- Listen, I'm really sorry.

49:28.704 --> 49:30.054
I didn't know-

49:30.141 --> 49:31.446
- Dad never should have
let you in this house.

49:31.533 --> 49:33.840
He didn't want to,
but mom made him.

49:33.927 --> 49:35.973
- He asked me to stay.

49:36.060 --> 49:38.062
- What, you think
you wanted you here?

49:38.149 --> 49:39.367
The only reason he's
letting you stay

49:39.454 --> 49:41.021
is because mom promised
to get rid of you

49:41.108 --> 49:43.197
first thing Monday morning.

49:43.284 --> 49:46.244
You are not a part of this
family and you never will be.

49:50.465 --> 49:53.033
[dramatic music]

50:07.439 --> 50:09.136
- I need to get in.

50:14.663 --> 50:19.146
[crying]
[sad music]

51:28.650 --> 51:30.087
- Finch!

51:33.177 --> 51:35.048
Finch!

51:37.311 --> 51:38.399
Finch!

51:42.186 --> 51:44.013
Did you stay out here all night?

51:44.101 --> 51:45.102
What's this?

51:47.582 --> 51:49.323
- I did what you said.

51:49.410 --> 51:52.065
I wrote down memories
of gran and pap

51:52.152 --> 51:53.501
so I'll always have them.

51:54.589 --> 51:56.069
- Finch, this is really good.

51:57.984 --> 51:59.681
You're an excellent writer.

52:01.074 --> 52:02.684
- You think so?

52:02.771 --> 52:03.685
- Yeah, I do.

52:05.209 --> 52:08.081
- But we better get you
inside, warm you up.

52:08.168 --> 52:09.691
Janelle has some
breakfast ready.

52:11.171 --> 52:12.216
- I can't go back.

52:13.913 --> 52:15.175
I've caused too much trouble.

52:18.352 --> 52:20.615
- Well, you can't stay here.

52:20.702 --> 52:22.269
We'll figure it out.

52:22.356 --> 52:23.966
It might take us a little
longer than expected,

52:24.053 --> 52:25.316
but we'll find you a home.

52:36.762 --> 52:38.894
- [Toby] I told you to
stay out of my room.

52:38.981 --> 52:39.939
- [Jackson] I
wasn't in your room.

52:40.026 --> 52:41.462
- Boys.

52:41.549 --> 52:42.507
- [Toby] Then why is
my hoodie on your bed?

52:42.594 --> 52:44.117
- [Jackson] I don't know.

52:44.204 --> 52:46.032
- Mom, can I go to Sophie's?

52:46.119 --> 52:46.859
- Have you finished
sweeping the porch?

52:46.946 --> 52:47.990
- [Toby] Is that my hat?

52:48.077 --> 52:50.079
- [Jackson] Get out of my room.

52:50.167 --> 52:51.646
- Not yet, I'll do it after.

52:51.733 --> 52:53.082
- You know the rules.

52:53.170 --> 52:54.083
- [Toby] Give them to me.

52:54.171 --> 52:55.563
- Boys, keep it down.

52:55.650 --> 52:56.782
Not until your chores are done.

52:56.869 --> 52:58.436
- It'll be too late then.

52:58.523 --> 53:00.046
- Mom, Toby hit me.

53:00.133 --> 53:01.961
- I did not, you're such a baby.

53:02.048 --> 53:02.744
- Mom please.

53:02.831 --> 53:03.963
- Enough!

53:04.050 --> 53:05.573
Your dad is writing.

53:05.660 --> 53:08.010
Jack, go outside and play.

53:08.097 --> 53:10.012
Toby, go into Jack's room,

53:10.099 --> 53:12.014
get your things out of there
and apologize for hitting him.

53:12.101 --> 53:13.668
Lisa, chores first.

53:13.755 --> 53:14.626
- Okay.

53:14.713 --> 53:15.844
- I didn't touch him.

53:15.931 --> 53:17.890
- I never get to go anywhere.

53:17.977 --> 53:20.066
[scoffs]

53:22.329 --> 53:24.113
- What you doing?

53:24.201 --> 53:25.245
- Recollecting.

53:25.332 --> 53:26.855
- What's that mean?

53:26.942 --> 53:28.248
- It means I'm writing down

53:28.335 --> 53:30.032
things that happened
in the past.

53:30.119 --> 53:31.469
- Like stories?

53:31.556 --> 53:32.731
- Memories.

53:32.818 --> 53:34.080
- Will you tell me one?

53:34.167 --> 53:34.602
- Sure.

53:36.082 --> 53:38.476
- Lisa, Finch is
gonna tell me a story.

53:38.563 --> 53:39.955
You want to hear it?

53:40.042 --> 53:41.087
- Why not?

53:42.480 --> 53:45.222
- Well, this one is about

53:45.309 --> 53:48.312
when my gran was laid up in bed

53:48.399 --> 53:50.052
and pap had to make the lye soap

53:50.139 --> 53:51.489
by himself for the first time.

53:54.535 --> 53:56.102
- Will you look at that?

53:56.189 --> 53:58.800
- Yeah, they've been at
it for almost an hour now.

53:58.887 --> 54:00.193
- No arguing and fighting.

54:00.280 --> 54:01.934
- I know, I can't
believe it either.

54:03.457 --> 54:05.459
I just wish Toby was
out there with them.

54:06.547 --> 54:08.201
- What about us?

54:08.288 --> 54:09.942
Why aren't we out
there with them?

54:10.029 --> 54:11.073
- Good question.

54:12.205 --> 54:13.772
[laughing]

54:13.859 --> 54:15.904
I can't believe that
really happened.

54:15.991 --> 54:17.950
- Come on Finch, tell
them about the lye soap.

54:18.037 --> 54:19.299
That one's really funny.

54:19.386 --> 54:20.822
- Finch might need
to take a break.

54:20.909 --> 54:22.302
He's been at it for a while now.

54:22.389 --> 54:24.391
- I'm so glad you're
writing these down.

54:24.478 --> 54:26.306
These are priceless memories.

54:26.393 --> 54:28.569
- Well, my pap was
the storyteller.

54:28.656 --> 54:30.179
After dinner, we
would sit on the porch

54:30.267 --> 54:33.922
and he would weave gran
and I the wildest tales

54:34.009 --> 54:36.621
and we would laugh until
we had tears in our eyes.

54:36.708 --> 54:38.623
And he always swore
they were all true,

54:38.710 --> 54:40.277
but after he passed,

54:40.364 --> 54:42.104
gran told me that he
would just make them up

54:42.191 --> 54:43.280
while he was doing his chores.

54:44.846 --> 54:47.066
- You should write your
pap's stories down too.

54:47.153 --> 54:49.677
- You can make a whole
book out of them.

54:49.764 --> 54:51.244
- I think he would
have liked that.

54:51.331 --> 54:53.028
- [Janelle] I'm sure
he'd be so proud

54:53.115 --> 54:55.640
to know his stories are
still making people happy.

54:55.727 --> 54:57.946
- Looks like you're gonna
need some more journals

54:58.033 --> 54:59.600
or maybe a laptop computer.

54:59.687 --> 55:01.036
- No.

55:01.123 --> 55:03.082
Thank you, I will
stick to my pencils.

55:03.169 --> 55:05.432
[laughing]

55:07.086 --> 55:09.131
- Yes, that is correct.

55:13.397 --> 55:14.180
Uh huh.

55:17.139 --> 55:20.186
Yes, well, Marguerite.

55:20.273 --> 55:21.666
Hey, let me call you back.

55:22.797 --> 55:24.408
What are you doing here?

55:24.495 --> 55:27.324
- I know how eager you are to
find a placement for Finch.

55:27.411 --> 55:31.371
- Well, we were, but things
went really well this weekend.

55:31.458 --> 55:33.330
Keith and I talked
about it last night

55:33.417 --> 55:34.635
and if you can't find a family-

55:34.722 --> 55:35.984
- Oh but I already have,

55:36.071 --> 55:37.508
that's what I came
by to tell you.

55:37.595 --> 55:40.032
Finch's birth mother
contacted CPS.

55:40.119 --> 55:42.164
- His birth mother?

55:42.251 --> 55:43.340
But we don't know who she is?

55:43.427 --> 55:44.863
- We do now.

55:44.950 --> 55:47.126
She came by with two
attorneys and a full affidavit

55:47.213 --> 55:48.867
explaining everything
that happened

55:48.954 --> 55:50.869
down to the smallest detail.

55:50.956 --> 55:53.132
She's even consented
to a blood test.

55:53.219 --> 55:54.960
It's definitely her.

55:55.047 --> 55:57.876
And she wants full custody.

55:57.963 --> 56:00.008
So you and Keith
are off the hook.

56:00.095 --> 56:02.010
- Why is she showing up now?

56:02.097 --> 56:05.013
Where has she been
for the last 16 years?

56:05.100 --> 56:07.015
- I thought you'd
be happy about this.

56:07.102 --> 56:09.496
- She abandoned
him with strangers

56:09.583 --> 56:12.499
and didn't contact
him for 16 years.

56:12.586 --> 56:15.502
Excuse me for questioning
her character.

56:15.589 --> 56:17.069
- Oh, Janelle.

56:17.156 --> 56:20.115
Please tell me, you're not
gonna try and fight this.

56:20.202 --> 56:21.726
- And what happens if we do?

56:23.945 --> 56:25.991
- The judge would
hear both parties

56:26.078 --> 56:28.080
and make a determination.

56:28.167 --> 56:30.125
But I have to warn you, Janelle,

56:30.212 --> 56:34.260
the law heavily favors the birth
mother in these situations.

56:34.347 --> 56:35.435
- Well, I don't.

56:35.522 --> 56:37.132
- What happened?

56:37.219 --> 56:39.221
I thought that you wanted to
find a permanent home for him.

56:39.308 --> 56:40.614
- I do.

56:40.701 --> 56:42.790
I just want to make
sure it's the right one.

56:44.488 --> 56:45.576
[sighs]

56:54.236 --> 56:56.978
- Okay, so what
do we tell Finch?

56:57.065 --> 56:58.458
- Nothing for now.

56:58.545 --> 57:01.026
Anything could happen
before the judge's ruling?

57:01.113 --> 57:04.203
I mean she could decide
to disappear again.

57:04.290 --> 57:05.900
- It's better not
to get his hopes up

57:05.987 --> 57:08.163
until we know
something for certain.

57:08.250 --> 57:10.470
Will the judge let him stay
with us until the hearing?

57:10.557 --> 57:12.254
- Do you want him to?

57:12.341 --> 57:13.821
It could take weeks.

57:13.908 --> 57:15.301
- He's already here.

57:15.388 --> 57:17.085
We don't want to
move him around again

57:17.172 --> 57:19.174
and it's only for
a little while.

57:21.481 --> 57:24.745
- Are we crazy for
getting mixed up in this?

57:24.832 --> 57:27.095
- It's a little late
for that, isn't it?

57:27.182 --> 57:28.967
Could you walk
away from this now?

57:29.054 --> 57:32.579
- No.

57:32.666 --> 57:35.756
- Could you?

57:35.843 --> 57:37.149
- No.

57:37.236 --> 57:38.890
[soft music]

57:40.065 --> 57:41.458
- Thank you.

57:41.545 --> 57:42.328
- For what?

57:44.591 --> 57:47.246
- For just being you.

57:51.642 --> 57:53.034
- Did you pack my jello?

57:53.121 --> 57:54.906
- [Janelle] Strawberry,
it's in your bag.

57:54.993 --> 57:55.776
- Yes!

57:58.779 --> 58:01.129
- I'm going to Dina's after
school to do homework.

58:01.216 --> 58:02.174
- Will her mom be home?

58:02.261 --> 58:03.305
- [Lisa] Uh huh.

58:04.742 --> 58:06.526
- Drake's big
brother will be home.

58:06.613 --> 58:08.572
- Nice try but we
talked about this,

58:08.659 --> 58:10.661
straight home from school
to do your homework.

58:10.748 --> 58:13.011
You can play "Hunter's Watch"
with Drake next Saturday.

58:13.098 --> 58:14.534
- Lisa gets to go.

58:14.621 --> 58:16.188
- Sorry, that's
how it is for now.

58:19.147 --> 58:20.018
- Looking sharp.

58:21.846 --> 58:23.151
- First day of school
for Finch, mom,

58:23.238 --> 58:24.065
take a picture.

58:24.152 --> 58:25.545
- We're gonna be late.

58:25.632 --> 58:27.852
- Nope, Jack's right,
it's tradition.

58:27.939 --> 58:30.028
We always take a picture
of the first day of school.

58:30.115 --> 58:31.203
- It's not my first
day of school.

58:31.290 --> 58:32.378
I'll be in the car.

58:32.465 --> 58:33.814
- Toby.

58:33.901 --> 58:36.991
Okay, come on,
everybody, move in close.

58:40.038 --> 58:41.343
Got it.

58:41.430 --> 58:42.954
- Get in the car,
it's time to go.

58:48.916 --> 58:50.004
Are you ready for this?

58:50.091 --> 58:52.180
- I think so.

58:52.267 --> 58:54.269
I don't really know
what it will be like.

58:56.141 --> 58:57.359
- Just be yourself.

58:57.446 --> 58:59.013
Be friendly.

58:59.100 --> 59:01.059
Don't make too many A's
on your first day though.

59:01.146 --> 59:03.540
Lisa is accustomed to being
the smartest one in the family.

59:03.627 --> 59:05.106
- Oh stop.

59:05.193 --> 59:06.978
Don't be afraid to ask questions

59:07.065 --> 59:10.590
and remember Toby will be there
to help you find everything.

59:10.677 --> 59:11.765
- I'll be fine.

59:11.852 --> 59:13.027
Thank you.

59:13.114 --> 59:14.551
- Well, get in the car then.

59:14.638 --> 59:16.074
We can't be late
for your first day.

59:17.249 --> 59:19.773
[jaunty music]

59:32.612 --> 59:34.179
- I am sorry I'm late, youngins,

59:34.266 --> 59:36.921
but I lost my glasses
in the teacher's lounge.

59:37.008 --> 59:41.665
But fear not, I have another
pair here in my bag somewhere.

59:41.752 --> 59:44.145
Oh here they are,
a bit dirty but,

59:44.232 --> 59:45.843
we'll clean 'em up.

59:45.930 --> 59:49.629
Oh, it looks like the ground
flew up there for a minute.

59:49.716 --> 59:52.632
Oh, I hope you did
your reading for today

59:52.719 --> 59:55.243
because I'm gonna be passing
out a quiz on chapter 46.

59:55.330 --> 59:56.941
[groaning]

59:57.028 --> 1:00:01.598
Oh ooh, oh, we have a unique
new student with us today.

1:00:01.685 --> 1:00:06.341
Join me in welcoming,
Mr. French Wagemaker.

1:00:07.125 --> 1:00:08.561
Mr. Wagemaker.

1:00:10.128 --> 1:00:12.173
French, why don't you
come up and join us

1:00:12.260 --> 1:00:13.871
so we all know who you are?

1:00:15.437 --> 1:00:17.614
[Whispers] They said he
might be a little slow.

1:00:19.224 --> 1:00:21.705
French, why don't you come
up to the front please?

1:00:22.662 --> 1:00:23.620
- Me?

1:00:23.707 --> 1:00:26.100
- Yes, come to the front please.

1:00:29.190 --> 1:00:32.106
Everybody, this is
French Wagemaker.

1:00:32.193 --> 1:00:34.543
He's never been to a
proper school before

1:00:34.631 --> 1:00:36.197
on account of he
grew up on a mountain

1:00:36.284 --> 1:00:38.112
far away from normal people.

1:00:38.199 --> 1:00:40.071
[laughing]

1:00:40.158 --> 1:00:42.813
[Shouting] On a mountain, right?

1:00:44.162 --> 1:00:46.686
Well I'll be, isn't that nice?

1:00:46.773 --> 1:00:48.470
Oh, everybody join me

1:00:48.557 --> 1:00:51.473
in making French feel
at home in our school.

1:00:51.560 --> 1:00:53.780
[clapping]

1:00:56.261 --> 1:00:59.133
[Shouting] You can
sit down now, honey.

1:00:59.220 --> 1:01:00.439
[Laughter]
Sit.

1:01:02.136 --> 1:01:05.052
As soon as we read the quote
of the day up on the board,

1:01:05.139 --> 1:01:07.751
we'll jump right into that quiz.

1:01:07.838 --> 1:01:08.665
All righty then.

1:01:10.231 --> 1:01:13.365
Oh since this is French's
very first day with us,

1:01:13.452 --> 1:01:16.150
why don't we have him
read the quote of the day

1:01:16.237 --> 1:01:19.110
and give us his opinion?

1:01:19.197 --> 1:01:23.288
[Shouting] French, read aloud
the quote for us, please.

1:01:25.203 --> 1:01:28.162
[students laughing]

1:01:31.078 --> 1:01:32.471
Oh boy.

1:01:32.558 --> 1:01:35.604
I'm sorry, I didn't mean
to embarrass you, honey.

1:01:35.692 --> 1:01:38.085
They told me you could read.

1:01:38.172 --> 1:01:39.957
[laughing]

1:01:40.044 --> 1:01:42.089
- No school should ever
try to serve meatloaf.

1:01:42.176 --> 1:01:44.962
- I swear, Miss Davenport's
trying to kill us.

1:01:45.049 --> 1:01:47.486
- So where is he?

1:01:47.573 --> 1:01:49.357
- He went to go
find the bathroom.

1:01:49.444 --> 1:01:52.143
- Yeah, but that
was 20 minutes ago.

1:01:52.230 --> 1:01:53.274
- This is ridiculous.

1:01:53.361 --> 1:01:55.189
We have to babysit him all day.

1:01:55.276 --> 1:01:57.496
- I'm not babysitting anyone.

1:01:57.583 --> 1:01:58.540
- Thanks for the help.

1:01:58.627 --> 1:02:01.152
- Hey, he seems like a nice guy.

1:02:01.239 --> 1:02:03.197
Maybe a little clueless.

1:02:03.284 --> 1:02:04.633
- A little brainless, too.

1:02:06.548 --> 1:02:09.290
- Hey, are you
really a hillbilly?

1:02:09.377 --> 1:02:11.292
- I don't really
know what that is.

1:02:11.379 --> 1:02:12.990
- Don't be rude.
- What?

1:02:13.077 --> 1:02:13.991
- How long did
you live up there?

1:02:14.078 --> 1:02:14.905
- On the mountain?

1:02:14.992 --> 1:02:16.428
I was born there.

1:02:16.515 --> 1:02:18.082
- So was their an entire
village of mountain people

1:02:18.169 --> 1:02:18.996
or just you?

1:02:19.083 --> 1:02:20.824
- Just me and my gran.

1:02:20.911 --> 1:02:22.739
- Did you grow up wearing
nothing but a loincloth

1:02:22.826 --> 1:02:23.652
like Tarzan?

1:02:23.740 --> 1:02:24.653
- I didn't-

1:02:24.741 --> 1:02:26.220
- You didn't have a loincloth?

1:02:26.307 --> 1:02:28.440
- Cut it out, guys.

1:02:28.527 --> 1:02:31.008
- What, does he
have a fan club now?

1:02:31.095 --> 1:02:32.574
- People are just curious.

1:02:32.661 --> 1:02:35.099
- He grew up in the
woods, big deal.

1:02:35.186 --> 1:02:38.406
- Uh oh, someone sounds
a little jealous.

1:02:38.493 --> 1:02:40.104
- Don't start with me, man.

1:02:40.191 --> 1:02:42.280
- You don't know who
Tarzan is, do you?

1:02:42.367 --> 1:02:43.803
- No.

1:02:43.890 --> 1:02:47.024
- So have you ever been
on the internet before?

1:02:47.111 --> 1:02:48.852
- I have a fishing net.

1:02:48.939 --> 1:02:50.462
My pap and I made it.

1:02:50.549 --> 1:02:51.680
- Pap?

1:02:51.768 --> 1:02:52.725
He's got a pap.

1:02:52.812 --> 1:02:53.900
- Well, actually-

1:02:53.987 --> 1:02:55.293
- That is so hillbilly.

1:02:55.380 --> 1:02:57.774
- So did you fish
and hunt for food?

1:02:57.861 --> 1:02:59.123
- That's cool.

1:02:59.210 --> 1:03:01.081
I mean, it's crazy,
but it's cool.

1:03:01.168 --> 1:03:02.126
- How is that cool?

1:03:02.213 --> 1:03:03.823
- Well, maybe not to you, Caleb,

1:03:03.910 --> 1:03:06.173
but you wouldn't last more
than five minutes in the wild.

1:03:06.260 --> 1:03:08.262
- Shut up.
- That's so true, though.

1:03:08.349 --> 1:03:09.481
- Thanks for talking with me.

1:03:09.568 --> 1:03:11.135
Nice to meet you all.

1:03:20.274 --> 1:03:22.102
- Hurry up, you're
gonna make us late.

1:03:25.018 --> 1:03:26.759
- What do you have on your arm?

1:03:26.846 --> 1:03:28.848
- It's my locker combination.

1:03:28.935 --> 1:03:30.894
A girl wrote it on there for me.

1:03:30.981 --> 1:03:33.113
- That's not a
locker combination.

1:03:33.200 --> 1:03:33.940
- Hurry up and get changed.

1:03:34.027 --> 1:03:35.028
We have PE next.

1:03:37.030 --> 1:03:39.206
See what I mean, babysitting.

1:03:40.860 --> 1:03:41.861
He's fine.

1:03:41.948 --> 1:03:42.731
- Hold up.

1:03:43.907 --> 1:03:45.125
- You don't need to do that.

1:03:49.086 --> 1:03:50.087
- Bring your gym clothes.

1:03:50.174 --> 1:03:51.915
We are running today.

1:03:53.264 --> 1:03:54.656
Are you fast?

1:03:54.743 --> 1:03:56.093
- I think so.

1:03:56.180 --> 1:03:59.052
My gran and I never
really raced much.

1:03:59.139 --> 1:04:01.315
- Well, Toby's been the
fastest kid in our class

1:04:01.402 --> 1:04:02.882
since fifth grade.

1:04:02.969 --> 1:04:04.492
It's about time
somebody beat him.

1:04:06.016 --> 1:04:07.452
- What makes you
think he can beat me?

1:04:07.539 --> 1:04:09.193
- I don't know.

1:04:09.280 --> 1:04:11.412
This guy has been running around
a mountain his whole life.

1:04:11.499 --> 1:04:13.588
We spent six hours
playing "Hunter's Watch"

1:04:13.675 --> 1:04:16.200
and eating potato
chips last Saturday.

1:04:16.287 --> 1:04:17.636
I'd bet money on him.

1:04:19.681 --> 1:04:21.118
- That's everyone,
Coach Winklevoss.

1:04:21.205 --> 1:04:23.772
- All right, runners.

1:04:23.860 --> 1:04:25.165
Let's go.

1:04:25.252 --> 1:04:26.993
Let's get those
legs stretched out.

1:04:27.080 --> 1:04:28.995
[grumbling]

1:04:29.082 --> 1:04:31.519
And I don't want to
hear any complaining.

1:04:31.606 --> 1:04:33.608
Today is a beautiful
day for running.

1:04:47.361 --> 1:04:50.016
Okay, how do we feel back there?

1:04:50.103 --> 1:04:51.583
[grumbling]

1:04:51.670 --> 1:04:54.194
Since it's a new month,
we have a new challenge.

1:04:54.281 --> 1:04:57.328
The student who has the
fastest cumulative time

1:04:57.415 --> 1:04:59.156
in the 100 meter dash

1:04:59.243 --> 1:05:03.116
will win four tickets
to the Cineplex Theater.

1:05:03.203 --> 1:05:04.988
[Grumbling]
[Kid] Just four?

1:05:05.075 --> 1:05:07.120
What, you don't like movies?

1:05:07.207 --> 1:05:09.427
- You may as well
hand them to Toby now.

1:05:09.514 --> 1:05:11.298
Save us all a lot
of embarrassment.

1:05:11.385 --> 1:05:12.734
[Girl] Yeah, it'd save time.

1:05:12.821 --> 1:05:14.475
- Oh, come on now.

1:05:14.562 --> 1:05:16.216
That's the wrong attitude.

1:05:16.303 --> 1:05:17.261
You gotta work for it.

1:05:18.349 --> 1:05:20.394
Strive to be better every day.

1:05:21.656 --> 1:05:22.483
[whistle blowing]

1:05:22.570 --> 1:05:23.397
Line 'em up, people.

1:05:23.484 --> 1:05:25.182
First group of five.

1:05:25.269 --> 1:05:27.924
[upbeat music]

1:05:40.023 --> 1:05:40.762
- On your marks,

1:05:42.068 --> 1:05:43.287
get set,
[dramatic music]

1:05:43.374 --> 1:05:44.201
go.

1:05:44.288 --> 1:05:47.073
[kids cheering]

1:05:47.160 --> 1:05:49.032
- You can do it, Finch.

1:05:51.643 --> 1:05:53.993
- Come on Toby,
you can take him.

1:05:54.080 --> 1:05:56.517
[upbeat music]

1:05:56.604 --> 1:06:00.434
[crowd shouts disapprovingly]

1:06:04.221 --> 1:06:05.309
- [Girl] Are you okay?

1:06:05.396 --> 1:06:06.353
- Easy, easy.

1:06:06.440 --> 1:06:07.833
- [Girl] Oh my gosh, okay, okay.

1:06:07.920 --> 1:06:09.313
It's gonna be okay.
- Let's lift him up.

1:06:09.400 --> 1:06:13.534
Okay, stand, there you
go, up, easy, okay.

1:06:13.621 --> 1:06:14.883
Here we go.

1:06:14.971 --> 1:06:15.884
Here we go.

1:06:17.843 --> 1:06:19.279
- What kind of cheap
shot was that, dude?

1:06:19.366 --> 1:06:20.150
- We just bumped.

1:06:20.237 --> 1:06:21.238
It happens.

1:06:22.239 --> 1:06:23.544
- Don't worry, kids,

1:06:23.631 --> 1:06:24.981
I think he'll be okay.

1:06:25.068 --> 1:06:25.982
- What?

1:06:26.069 --> 1:06:26.983
- [Girl] What was that?

1:06:27.070 --> 1:06:27.679
- I won fair and square.

1:06:27.766 --> 1:06:28.593
- Jerk move.

1:06:28.680 --> 1:06:29.681
- It was an accident.

1:06:31.988 --> 1:06:33.685
What's their problem?

1:06:33.772 --> 1:06:34.555
Where are you going?

1:06:34.642 --> 1:06:36.035
- I'm going to make sure

1:06:36.122 --> 1:06:38.124
he knows where the
bathroom is this time.

1:06:38.211 --> 1:06:40.300
Try not to kick anyone
else while I'm gone.

1:06:48.613 --> 1:06:51.355
- Look at you,
hitting the books.

1:06:51.442 --> 1:06:53.096
- Not like I have a choice.

1:06:53.183 --> 1:06:54.532
I'm grounded, remember?

1:06:57.013 --> 1:06:57.796
- I do.

1:07:05.151 --> 1:07:07.066
You know, I was thinking,

1:07:07.153 --> 1:07:10.287
next weekend, maybe
we should go camping.

1:07:10.374 --> 1:07:13.029
Get some fresh air,
clear our heads a bit.

1:07:14.117 --> 1:07:15.074
- Really?

1:07:15.161 --> 1:07:17.294
- Yeah, it's been a long time.

1:07:17.381 --> 1:07:19.600
I could finally teach
you how to fish.

1:07:19.687 --> 1:07:22.212
- Yeah, okay.

1:07:22.299 --> 1:07:24.692
- My rods are too
big for Jack, though.

1:07:24.779 --> 1:07:27.086
We'll have to stop and pick
up a smaller one for him.

1:07:28.044 --> 1:07:29.567
- Jack?

1:07:29.654 --> 1:07:31.177
- Though Finch says he
makes his own fishing rods

1:07:31.264 --> 1:07:32.787
out of tree branches.

1:07:32.874 --> 1:07:34.224
He could teach us
how to do that.

1:07:34.311 --> 1:07:35.877
- I can't.

1:07:35.964 --> 1:07:37.836
I told Drake I'd
meet him on Saturday.

1:07:37.923 --> 1:07:39.316
- Oh, come on.

1:07:39.403 --> 1:07:40.969
You can't miss a few
hours of video games

1:07:41.057 --> 1:07:42.884
for a camping trip
with your family?

1:07:42.971 --> 1:07:43.755
- Family?

1:07:44.756 --> 1:07:46.192
- You know what?

1:07:46.279 --> 1:07:47.585
I'm getting tired
of your attitude.

1:07:47.672 --> 1:07:49.326
You are part of a family

1:07:49.413 --> 1:07:50.762
and being part of a family

1:07:50.849 --> 1:07:53.417
means you take time and
invest in your family.

1:07:53.504 --> 1:07:54.896
- I'm going to
finish in my room.

1:07:54.983 --> 1:07:56.681
- No, you're always
hiding in your room.

1:07:56.768 --> 1:07:59.249
You need to be down here
interacting with the rest of us.

1:07:59.336 --> 1:08:02.165
It's not so healthy for you to
be so isolated all the time.

1:08:02.252 --> 1:08:03.949
- Oh, so now I'm not
healthy, is that it?

1:08:04.036 --> 1:08:06.343
- I just want you to
make a stronger effort

1:08:06.430 --> 1:08:08.345
to be part of the
family, that's all.

1:08:08.432 --> 1:08:10.782
- Sorry to be such a
disappointment to you.

1:08:10.869 --> 1:08:13.785
- Hey, look at me, look at me.

1:08:13.872 --> 1:08:15.656
That is not how I feel.

1:08:15.743 --> 1:08:17.005
You are my son.

1:08:17.093 --> 1:08:18.529
- Just not the one you wanted.

1:08:18.616 --> 1:08:20.226
- What?

1:08:20.313 --> 1:08:22.010
- That's why you went out and
found another one, isn't it?

1:08:22.098 --> 1:08:23.534
That's why you went
out and got Jack,

1:08:23.621 --> 1:08:25.710
only I guess he didn't
fit the bill either.

1:08:25.797 --> 1:08:26.667
- Is that what you think?

1:08:26.754 --> 1:08:28.060
- Now you've got Finch.

1:08:28.147 --> 1:08:29.627
You've finally found
your kind of kid.

1:08:29.714 --> 1:08:30.671
Now you guys can go fishing

1:08:30.758 --> 1:08:32.238
and write best sellers together.

1:08:32.325 --> 1:08:33.326
- Toby.

1:08:34.240 --> 1:08:37.069
[phone ringing]

1:08:38.288 --> 1:08:39.593
Yeah?

1:08:39.680 --> 1:08:40.855
- [Janelle] Keith,
we have a problem.

1:08:42.335 --> 1:08:43.380
- Come on, Drake.

1:08:43.467 --> 1:08:44.511
You can't get out of it?

1:08:44.598 --> 1:08:46.122
We've had this plan for awhile.

1:08:47.993 --> 1:08:51.997
Okay look, this isn't about
what happened at school, right?

1:08:53.955 --> 1:08:56.001
Yeah, no, I get it.

1:08:56.088 --> 1:08:57.263
Maybe a movie on Sunday?

1:08:59.352 --> 1:09:01.137
Yeah, sure, some
other time then.

1:09:07.752 --> 1:09:09.580
[Dramatic music]

1:09:30.818 --> 1:09:32.168
- Marguerite.

1:09:32.255 --> 1:09:33.995
- Janelle.

1:09:34.082 --> 1:09:36.041
- Listen, there's
something wrong here.

1:09:36.128 --> 1:09:38.261
Something is off about
this whole thing.

1:09:38.348 --> 1:09:41.568
- Look Janelle, this really
isn't your call to make.

1:09:41.655 --> 1:09:44.136
Finch's mother insisted
on temporary custody

1:09:44.223 --> 1:09:45.529
until the hearing.

1:09:45.616 --> 1:09:46.660
The judge is granting it.

1:09:46.747 --> 1:09:48.314
- But why so fast?

1:09:48.401 --> 1:09:51.230
She hasn't shown any interest
in him since he was born

1:09:51.317 --> 1:09:54.015
and now all of a sudden she
can't live a day without him.

1:09:54.102 --> 1:09:56.017
- Maybe she didn't
know where he was.

1:09:56.104 --> 1:09:58.194
- He was right where
she abandoned him.

1:09:58.281 --> 1:10:00.892
- Maybe she finally has
her life in a good place

1:10:00.979 --> 1:10:02.850
and can support him.

1:10:02.937 --> 1:10:03.982
- Has she been in jail?

1:10:05.113 --> 1:10:06.506
- You know I can't answer that.

1:10:06.593 --> 1:10:09.205
- But you said she came
here with two attorneys.

1:10:09.292 --> 1:10:12.338
Who hires two attorneys for
a family custody hearing?

1:10:12.425 --> 1:10:14.688
- I can't say anything more.

1:10:14.775 --> 1:10:17.038
- She's either ridiculously rich

1:10:17.125 --> 1:10:20.346
or someone else is helping
her out, a family member.

1:10:20.433 --> 1:10:22.435
- Janelle, I cannot
talk to you about this.

1:10:22.522 --> 1:10:24.002
- How was she dressed?

1:10:24.089 --> 1:10:25.264
Was she really put together?

1:10:25.351 --> 1:10:26.744
- Janelle.

1:10:26.831 --> 1:10:28.267
- I'm not asking for
state secrets here.

1:10:28.354 --> 1:10:30.487
I'm asking you woman to woman.

1:10:30.574 --> 1:10:32.053
Did she look like she had money?

1:10:33.403 --> 1:10:35.100
- No.

1:10:35.187 --> 1:10:39.060
- Then how can she hire
a team of attorneys?

1:10:39.147 --> 1:10:40.975
- Are we done here, detective?

1:10:42.194 --> 1:10:43.326
- Yeah.

1:10:43.413 --> 1:10:45.328
No one more thing.

1:10:45.415 --> 1:10:47.025
When she came into your office,

1:10:47.112 --> 1:10:50.333
was she calm and composed
or fidgety and nervous?

1:10:50.420 --> 1:10:53.031
- I'd say more nervous,
but that's not uncommon.

1:10:53.118 --> 1:10:56.817
- Okay, a picture is
starting to take shape here.

1:10:56.904 --> 1:10:59.037
The mother is not driving this.

1:10:59.124 --> 1:11:02.214
The attorneys are bringing
her along, but why?

1:11:02.301 --> 1:11:04.608
- I'm leaving now.

1:11:04.695 --> 1:11:07.654
Who would stand to gain
anything monetarily

1:11:07.741 --> 1:11:09.830
from Finch living
with his mother?

1:11:09.917 --> 1:11:11.267
He has nothing of value.

1:11:11.354 --> 1:11:13.094
Believe me, I saw the cabin.

1:11:17.664 --> 1:11:21.015
Marguerite, did the
Whittaker's own the land

1:11:21.102 --> 1:11:24.932
up on Briar Rock or were
they just squatters?

1:11:25.019 --> 1:11:26.282
- I have no idea.

1:11:27.457 --> 1:11:29.067
- It's time to do some digging.

1:11:30.416 --> 1:11:32.549
- We never had
this conversation.

1:11:34.464 --> 1:11:36.988
- If two women discussing
another woman's
outfit is illegal,

1:11:37.075 --> 1:11:40.034
half the women in the world
would be in jail right now.

1:11:40.121 --> 1:11:43.603
- Remind me to never
get on your bad side.

1:12:00.925 --> 1:12:03.449
[ominous music]

1:12:17.811 --> 1:12:19.204
- The treehouse.

1:12:20.248 --> 1:12:22.729
[dark music]

1:12:38.049 --> 1:12:39.659
What are you doing?

1:12:39.746 --> 1:12:42.009
- Just burning some trash.

1:12:44.360 --> 1:12:46.666
- My bird, it was on the porch.

1:12:46.753 --> 1:12:47.493
Have you seen it?

1:12:49.887 --> 1:12:50.757
- Why are you here?

1:12:52.237 --> 1:12:53.020
This isn't your home.

1:12:54.935 --> 1:12:57.851
The worst day of my life is
the day you showed up here.

1:12:57.938 --> 1:12:59.331
If it weren't for you,

1:12:59.418 --> 1:13:01.681
the kids at school
wouldn't be mad at me,

1:13:01.768 --> 1:13:03.814
Drake wouldn't be mad at me,

1:13:03.901 --> 1:13:05.381
Dad would still have his book.

1:13:07.295 --> 1:13:09.123
The bird made a good starter.

1:13:13.084 --> 1:13:14.999
- That was my gran's bird.

1:13:16.740 --> 1:13:18.350
Why would you do that?

1:13:18.437 --> 1:13:20.221
- I had to start the
fire with something.

1:13:21.397 --> 1:13:23.137
How else could I burn your book?

1:13:24.835 --> 1:13:26.706
- You burned my journal?

1:13:26.793 --> 1:13:28.795
- Only seemed fair that if
Dad should lose his book,

1:13:28.882 --> 1:13:30.580
you should lose yours.

1:13:32.277 --> 1:13:33.626
Come on hillbilly, hit me.

1:13:35.149 --> 1:13:36.977
Let's show everyone what
you're really made of.

1:13:38.022 --> 1:13:40.198
What, you miss your family?

1:13:41.242 --> 1:13:43.593
Now you know how I feel.

1:13:43.680 --> 1:13:44.594
- No, I don't.

1:13:46.204 --> 1:13:47.510
My family was taken from me.

1:13:48.989 --> 1:13:50.991
You're just walking
away from yours.

1:13:52.166 --> 1:13:54.691
[dark music]

1:13:58.042 --> 1:13:59.435
[fire crackling]

1:14:32.685 --> 1:14:34.078
- Finch!
- Finch!

1:14:36.210 --> 1:14:37.821
- [Janelle] Finch!

1:14:56.753 --> 1:14:58.972
- Hey Finch, can we talk
to you for a minute?

1:15:00.583 --> 1:15:01.279
- Sure.

1:15:02.672 --> 1:15:06.023
- I received some information.

1:15:07.111 --> 1:15:08.286
It's about your mother.

1:15:09.113 --> 1:15:11.158
- My mom?

1:15:11.245 --> 1:15:13.770
- She came to CPS
looking for you.

1:15:13.857 --> 1:15:16.337
She's very interested
in meeting you.

1:15:16.424 --> 1:15:17.208
- She did?

1:15:18.862 --> 1:15:21.168
- Now we don't know
anything about her

1:15:21.255 --> 1:15:23.083
and we're not sure why
she's back right now,

1:15:23.170 --> 1:15:25.129
but we thought it'd be good

1:15:25.216 --> 1:15:27.566
if you met her and hear
what she had to say.

1:15:29.394 --> 1:15:32.266
- She wants you to come
live with her, Finch.

1:15:36.183 --> 1:15:36.923
- [Keith] Are you okay?

1:15:38.925 --> 1:15:40.536
- Live with my mom?

1:15:40.623 --> 1:15:43.016
- Yes, but nothing is definite.

1:15:43.103 --> 1:15:45.105
If you meet her and don't
want to go with her,

1:15:45.192 --> 1:15:47.151
we will fight it with
everything we have.

1:15:47.238 --> 1:15:48.239
- We don't want you
to live with her

1:15:48.326 --> 1:15:49.675
unless it's what you want.

1:15:53.505 --> 1:15:54.288
- Okay.

1:15:57.117 --> 1:15:58.336
When will I see her?

1:16:00.817 --> 1:16:01.992
- Tomorrow.

1:16:02.079 --> 1:16:02.993
- Tomorrow?

1:16:05.082 --> 1:16:09.042
I have school tomorrow and
I have to get homework done

1:16:09.129 --> 1:16:12.393
and I promised Jack I'd make
him a table for the tree house.

1:16:12.480 --> 1:16:14.352
- I know it's a
lot to think about.

1:16:14.439 --> 1:16:17.137
- You don't have to
decide anything right now.

1:16:17.224 --> 1:16:19.313
You can take your time
and think about it.

1:16:22.839 --> 1:16:23.579
- Yeah.

1:16:28.148 --> 1:16:30.716
Can I be alone for a minute?

1:16:30.803 --> 1:16:32.588
- Yes, of course.

1:16:51.650 --> 1:16:54.697
So it turns out the
Whittaker's weren't squatters.

1:16:54.784 --> 1:16:57.177
They owned the 125 acres of land

1:16:57.264 --> 1:16:59.179
on top of Briar Rock Mountain.

1:16:59.266 --> 1:17:01.921
Jeremiah Whitaker
inherited it in 1952

1:17:02.008 --> 1:17:04.358
and now it belongs to Finch,

1:17:04.445 --> 1:17:07.274
well to his guardian
anyway, until he turns 18.

1:17:07.361 --> 1:17:09.059
- Oh, that's great.

1:17:09.146 --> 1:17:11.017
That much land must be worth
a couple hundred thousand

1:17:11.104 --> 1:17:11.975
in today's money.

1:17:12.062 --> 1:17:14.107
- Try 2.5 million.

1:17:14.194 --> 1:17:15.805
- Million?

1:17:15.892 --> 1:17:17.284
- That's how much Alpha Gas
offered the Whittakers for it

1:17:17.371 --> 1:17:18.808
before they died.

1:17:18.895 --> 1:17:20.984
Apparently that land
is prime for fracking.

1:17:21.071 --> 1:17:23.987
- Finch is worth $2.5 million?

1:17:24.074 --> 1:17:27.599
- No, his guardian
is until he turns 18.

1:17:27.686 --> 1:17:28.948
And guess who knows about it?

1:17:29.035 --> 1:17:29.819
- No.

1:17:29.906 --> 1:17:31.168
- Enter his mother,

1:17:31.255 --> 1:17:33.692
armed to the teeth
with expensive lawyers.

1:17:33.779 --> 1:17:35.128
- Poor Finch.

1:17:35.215 --> 1:17:36.782
- Judge Raymond is
gonna get an earful

1:17:36.869 --> 1:17:38.175
about this at the hearing.

1:17:38.262 --> 1:17:40.133
- You can't say
anything about this.

1:17:40.220 --> 1:17:41.787
- I most certainly can.

1:17:41.874 --> 1:17:43.484
- No, you can't.

1:17:43.571 --> 1:17:44.747
Think about Finch.

1:17:44.834 --> 1:17:46.313
What would it do to him?

1:17:46.400 --> 1:17:48.185
His mother comes
back into his life

1:17:48.272 --> 1:17:51.362
and you're going to tell him
she's only here for his money?

1:17:51.449 --> 1:17:53.059
And what if she isn't?

1:17:53.146 --> 1:17:55.061
- Why else would she
suddenly show up?

1:17:55.148 --> 1:17:57.020
- We don't really
know why she's back.

1:17:57.107 --> 1:17:58.674
She may really want
to be with him.

1:18:00.240 --> 1:18:01.764
We can't interfere
in their relationship

1:18:01.851 --> 1:18:03.200
based solely on a hunch.

1:18:03.287 --> 1:18:05.855
- Keith, I don't
want her to hurt him.

1:18:05.942 --> 1:18:08.335
- We may not be
able to stop that.

1:18:08.422 --> 1:18:10.860
- Well I can't just stand
by and let it happen.

1:18:11.991 --> 1:18:13.166
What is that?

1:18:13.253 --> 1:18:14.167
What are you looking at?

1:18:14.254 --> 1:18:15.603
- Toby's grades.

1:18:15.691 --> 1:18:17.344
He's failing three classes.

1:18:19.956 --> 1:18:23.699
- He's pulling away from
everything, school, us.

1:18:23.786 --> 1:18:25.048
- It's my fault.

1:18:25.135 --> 1:18:26.179
He thinks I'm
disappointed in him.

1:18:26.266 --> 1:18:27.572
- But that's not true.

1:18:27.659 --> 1:18:29.443
- I know, but I
haven't done enough

1:18:29.530 --> 1:18:30.706
to convince him otherwise.

1:18:32.403 --> 1:18:35.580
- Sometimes it's hard for
him to let people love him.

1:18:35.667 --> 1:18:38.061
He's always been so
critical of himself.

1:18:39.410 --> 1:18:41.325
He's like his father that way.

1:18:44.589 --> 1:18:45.546
You'll talk to him?

1:18:47.679 --> 1:18:48.462
- Yeah.

1:18:52.118 --> 1:18:53.903
[Crickets chirping]

1:18:56.862 --> 1:18:59.430
- [Lisa] I don't think you're
supposed to be up there.

1:19:00.823 --> 1:19:03.347
- I think better up here.

1:19:03.434 --> 1:19:05.088
- Thinking about your mom?

1:19:08.656 --> 1:19:11.485
Do you remember
anything about her?

1:19:11.572 --> 1:19:13.139
- Not really.

1:19:13.226 --> 1:19:17.753
Every time that I think
that I can see her face,

1:19:18.797 --> 1:19:20.016
I wonder if it's really her.

1:19:21.931 --> 1:19:24.150
Maybe it's just something
I'm making up in my head.

1:19:25.586 --> 1:19:27.066
- Are you going
to live with her?

1:19:29.895 --> 1:19:30.853
- I guess that I should.

1:19:32.289 --> 1:19:33.638
- You could just
stay here with us.

1:19:33.725 --> 1:19:34.639
Mom and dad would let you,

1:19:34.726 --> 1:19:35.683
I heard them say so.

1:19:35.771 --> 1:19:37.250
- They did?

1:19:37.337 --> 1:19:38.991
- Sure, just tell them
that's what you want.

1:19:39.078 --> 1:19:41.602
- You see, that's the problem,

1:19:41.689 --> 1:19:43.735
it's not about what I want,

1:19:45.128 --> 1:19:47.434
it's about what
God wants for me.

1:19:47.521 --> 1:19:49.393
- Doesn't God care
how you feel about it?

1:19:51.438 --> 1:19:53.223
- Well I reckon he does.

1:19:55.355 --> 1:19:58.968
But he knows what's best
for me better than I do.

1:20:00.578 --> 1:20:02.188
- Well, I'm gonna tell
him it makes you sad

1:20:02.275 --> 1:20:05.148
and all he has to do to
fix it is let you stay.

1:20:05.235 --> 1:20:06.410
Then you'll be happy again.

1:20:09.239 --> 1:20:11.632
- Sometimes he chooses
not to fix things

1:20:13.069 --> 1:20:14.635
and I have to be
okay with that too.

1:20:16.072 --> 1:20:18.074
- Even if it means
you have to leave?

1:20:20.728 --> 1:20:22.078
- Whatever it means.

1:20:25.124 --> 1:20:28.171
I've put my trust in
Jesus my whole life.

1:20:29.172 --> 1:20:30.521
He hasn't let me down yet.

1:20:33.524 --> 1:20:35.221
If he says that I need to go,

1:20:37.049 --> 1:20:38.442
then I should joyfully.

1:20:40.400 --> 1:20:43.055
- Is this one of those trials
that makes you stronger?

1:20:47.494 --> 1:20:49.801
- I think so.

1:20:49.888 --> 1:20:51.281
- I don't like them very much.

1:20:53.457 --> 1:20:56.286
[sad music]

1:20:56.373 --> 1:20:57.374
- Me neither.

1:21:06.296 --> 1:21:08.472
- Hey, are you still
okay with this?

1:21:08.559 --> 1:21:09.865
- Yes ma'am.

1:21:09.952 --> 1:21:11.562
- If you need anything,
we're right here.

1:21:11.649 --> 1:21:12.868
We're not going anywhere.

1:21:12.955 --> 1:21:14.347
- Anytime you want to leave,

1:21:14.434 --> 1:21:16.132
just let us know and
we'll come get you.

1:21:17.263 --> 1:21:19.396
- Thank you both for everything.

1:21:23.835 --> 1:21:25.881
- [Keith] Come on, let's
move a little further away.

1:21:25.968 --> 1:21:27.447
- No, he might need us.

1:21:27.534 --> 1:21:30.015
- We can't just stand
here and stare at them.

1:21:30.102 --> 1:21:31.364
- He might need us.

1:21:32.844 --> 1:21:33.627
- There's a bench over there.

1:21:33.714 --> 1:21:34.672
Come on.

1:21:43.899 --> 1:21:47.990
- Oh, I never dreamed you'd
get so tall and handsome.

1:21:48.077 --> 1:21:48.599
Look at you.

1:21:50.122 --> 1:21:52.255
I've missed so much
of your growing up.

1:21:52.342 --> 1:21:53.865
- Why don't we step over here

1:21:53.952 --> 1:21:55.084
and let them speak
alone for a moment?

1:21:55.171 --> 1:21:56.476
- It's all right.

1:21:56.563 --> 1:21:59.001
Mr. Billings and his
associate represent me.

1:21:59.088 --> 1:22:01.481
- You need attorneys
to speak with your son?

1:22:01.568 --> 1:22:03.092
- Of course not.

1:22:03.179 --> 1:22:05.921
I just say the silliest
things sometimes.

1:22:06.008 --> 1:22:07.879
And I wouldn't want
to say or do anything

1:22:07.966 --> 1:22:10.969
that might mess up my chances
of getting my baby boy back.

1:22:24.243 --> 1:22:27.029
- I haven't been a
baby for a long time.

1:22:27.116 --> 1:22:28.508
- Of course you haven't.

1:22:28.595 --> 1:22:30.119
You're practically a man now.

1:22:36.168 --> 1:22:40.042
- Can we just talk alone, mom?

1:22:41.304 --> 1:22:42.827
- Maybe next time Finch.

1:22:44.046 --> 1:22:45.482
Besides, when this is all over,

1:22:45.569 --> 1:22:47.527
we'll have plenty of
time to talk alone.

1:22:49.007 --> 1:22:52.228
So tell me, do you like school?

1:22:52.315 --> 1:22:53.969
What subject is your favorite?

1:22:54.056 --> 1:22:57.407
- I like English,
literature especially.

1:22:57.494 --> 1:22:59.757
- I never cared much
for reading books.

1:22:59.844 --> 1:23:02.064
I'm really more of a
magazine girl myself.

1:23:02.151 --> 1:23:04.022
I just love looking
at the pictures

1:23:04.109 --> 1:23:05.632
and hearing about all
the Hollywood stars

1:23:05.719 --> 1:23:07.243
and their glamorous lives.

1:23:07.330 --> 1:23:08.766
With your good looks,

1:23:08.853 --> 1:23:10.811
you could be an actor
in Hollywood movies.

1:23:10.898 --> 1:23:12.639
And then you could
be one of those stars

1:23:12.726 --> 1:23:15.991
that takes his mom as a date
to the Academy Awards show.

1:23:16.078 --> 1:23:17.905
- I just saw my first
movie the other day.

1:23:17.993 --> 1:23:19.516
- Your first movie?

1:23:19.603 --> 1:23:21.170
Who's ever heard
of a 16 year old,

1:23:21.257 --> 1:23:23.128
who hasn't been to a movie?

1:23:23.215 --> 1:23:25.522
- They didn't have
movies up on Briar Rock.

1:23:27.915 --> 1:23:31.049
- Finch, I never meant
to leave you for so long.

1:23:31.136 --> 1:23:34.139
I just, well, I had to
take care of some things

1:23:34.226 --> 1:23:36.185
before I could come
back and get you.

1:23:36.272 --> 1:23:37.229
- What kind of things?

1:23:38.274 --> 1:23:39.884
- Important grownup things.

1:23:41.538 --> 1:23:44.106
- Well you just said that
I was practically grown.

1:23:44.193 --> 1:23:45.498
I'd like to know

1:23:45.585 --> 1:23:47.326
what kind of things you
had to take care of.

1:23:47.413 --> 1:23:49.154
- Finch, I saw to it

1:23:49.241 --> 1:23:51.374
that you had kind
folks to look after you

1:23:51.461 --> 1:23:53.985
and that is so much
more than I ever had.

1:23:54.072 --> 1:23:57.075
I have been fending for
myself for a long time,

1:23:57.162 --> 1:23:58.598
but not anymore.

1:23:58.685 --> 1:24:00.383
Now I have Mr. Billings
taking care of my business

1:24:00.470 --> 1:24:01.862
and you to look after me

1:24:01.949 --> 1:24:04.039
and I won't ever have
to be alone again

1:24:04.126 --> 1:24:06.998
because you'll be
there right by my side.

1:24:07.085 --> 1:24:08.695
Isn't that right, sugar,

1:24:08.782 --> 1:24:10.480
just you and me
taking on the world?

1:24:11.437 --> 1:24:12.525
- Yes, ma'am.

1:24:12.612 --> 1:24:14.136
- Well aren't you good mannered?

1:24:14.223 --> 1:24:15.528
Someone raised you right.

1:24:15.615 --> 1:24:17.095
- The Whittaker's raised me.

1:24:17.182 --> 1:24:17.965
- The Whittaker's?

1:24:19.358 --> 1:24:22.231
- Jeremiah and
Lila Mae Whittaker.

1:24:22.318 --> 1:24:25.060
That's who was taking care
of you when you left me.

1:24:25.147 --> 1:24:27.627
- Finch, let's not
dwell on the past.

1:24:27.714 --> 1:24:29.151
It's all so sad.

1:24:29.238 --> 1:24:31.109
Let's just keep our
eyes on the future.

1:24:31.196 --> 1:24:32.763
Tomorrow, you'll
come live with me.

1:24:34.460 --> 1:24:37.376
Now, my house is just a little
bump in the road right now

1:24:37.463 --> 1:24:39.117
but as soon as we sign
a few pieces of paper,

1:24:39.204 --> 1:24:40.510
we'll have plenty of money

1:24:40.597 --> 1:24:43.078
to buy a nice big studio
apartment downtown,

1:24:43.165 --> 1:24:45.167
right where all the action is.

1:24:45.254 --> 1:24:50.215
- I was hoping we could go to
the mountain, up to the cabin.

1:24:50.302 --> 1:24:52.130
I can show you
where I grew up and-

1:24:52.217 --> 1:24:56.395
- Oh honey, that old rickety
dump won't be there anymore.

1:24:56.482 --> 1:24:58.136
- What?

1:24:58.223 --> 1:25:00.443
- I mean we won't
be there anymore

1:25:00.530 --> 1:25:03.837
because we'll be out
doing exciting new things.

1:25:03.924 --> 1:25:07.145
It's time for you and me to
get out and see the world.

1:25:07.232 --> 1:25:09.974
Oh... it's hot out here.

1:25:11.497 --> 1:25:13.673
I have to get into
some air conditioning

1:25:13.760 --> 1:25:15.371
before my makeup
melts off my face.

1:25:15.458 --> 1:25:16.720
I'll see you tomorrow.

1:25:16.807 --> 1:25:17.634
Mr. Billings?

1:25:18.983 --> 1:25:20.419
- I'm not sure I want to go.

1:25:20.506 --> 1:25:22.204
- What?

1:25:22.291 --> 1:25:24.249
- I might rather stay with
the Brennan's for awhile

1:25:24.336 --> 1:25:25.990
just until the hearing.

1:25:26.077 --> 1:25:28.862
- Well, I'm sorry, dear,
but that's not the plan.

1:25:28.949 --> 1:25:30.995
The judge says you'll stay
with me until the hearing.

1:25:31.082 --> 1:25:33.519
- I don't think I want to.

1:25:33.606 --> 1:25:35.652
- Well, I'm not asking
you what you want.

1:25:35.739 --> 1:25:39.003
I'm telling you as your mother
I know what's best for you.

1:25:39.090 --> 1:25:40.961
You believe in the
good book, don't you?

1:25:41.048 --> 1:25:42.659
- Yes, ma'am.

1:25:42.746 --> 1:25:46.010
- Well, it says honor thy
father and thy mother.

1:25:47.272 --> 1:25:48.404
Well, I'm your mother,

1:25:48.491 --> 1:25:50.014
so you have to do what I say.

1:25:52.756 --> 1:25:54.061
- Yes, ma'am.

1:25:54.149 --> 1:25:55.280
- That's better.

1:25:56.629 --> 1:25:58.153
See you tomorrow.

1:25:58.240 --> 1:26:00.459
- You're still allowed another
30 minutes, Miss Hague.

1:26:00.546 --> 1:26:01.634
- We'll talk more next time.

1:26:01.721 --> 1:26:02.809
It's just too hot out.

1:26:02.896 --> 1:26:04.159
Bye sweetie see you soon.

1:26:24.527 --> 1:26:27.356
- So what do you think?

1:26:30.315 --> 1:26:31.577
- I don't know.

1:26:38.149 --> 1:26:40.456
- Do you want to see her again?

1:26:44.155 --> 1:26:45.852
- I'm going to live with her.

1:26:56.123 --> 1:26:57.168
- Okay.

1:27:01.477 --> 1:27:03.522
- Are you sure
that's what you want?

1:27:05.089 --> 1:27:08.875
You could take some more
time to think about it.

1:27:12.879 --> 1:27:15.099
- Thinking about it
won't change anything.

1:27:18.320 --> 1:27:21.018
[gentle music]

1:27:25.022 --> 1:27:25.588
- All right then.

1:27:27.067 --> 1:27:28.634
When we get back,
I'll call the judge

1:27:28.721 --> 1:27:31.681
and let him know
what you want to do.

1:27:45.564 --> 1:27:49.176
♪ Should the morning
last forever ♪

1:27:49.264 --> 1:27:53.703
♪ Waking till the end of time ♪

1:27:55.226 --> 1:27:58.708
♪ With a washed
out woven canvas ♪

1:27:58.795 --> 1:28:03.408
♪ Cleansing through
my worn out mind ♪

1:28:03.495 --> 1:28:07.282
♪ With the dead
of night inside ♪

1:28:07.369 --> 1:28:12.287
♪ But sunlight peeking
through my blinds ♪

1:28:14.550 --> 1:28:18.771
♪ Should the morning
last forever ♪

1:28:18.858 --> 1:28:22.601
♪ Well then maybe I'd be fine ♪

1:28:40.793 --> 1:28:43.666
♪ Should the morning
last forever ♪

1:28:43.753 --> 1:28:48.235
♪ I'd wait till
the end of time ♪

1:28:48.323 --> 1:28:52.544
♪ When that washed
out canvas cleanses ♪

1:28:52.631 --> 1:28:57.593
♪ Well it could leave me blind ♪

1:29:00.509 --> 1:29:03.990
♪ When the dead of
night's inside ♪

1:29:04.077 --> 1:29:08.734
♪ Well that's when stars ♪
come out to shine ♪

1:29:10.345 --> 1:29:14.436
♪ Should the morning
last forever ♪

1:29:15.654 --> 1:29:17.656
- Jack and I made this for you,

1:29:19.266 --> 1:29:21.007
you know, so you won't forget.

1:29:22.095 --> 1:29:24.446
- There's no chance of that.

1:29:24.533 --> 1:29:25.316
Thank you.

1:29:51.124 --> 1:29:52.299
Oh...

1:29:57.174 --> 1:29:59.132
I finished it.

1:29:59.219 --> 1:30:00.569
- It's yours.

1:30:00.656 --> 1:30:01.700
You should read it again.

1:30:01.787 --> 1:30:03.310
It's even better
the second time.

1:30:11.014 --> 1:30:13.103
[soft music]

1:30:34.951 --> 1:30:38.171
♪ When the sun is passing over ♪

1:30:38.258 --> 1:30:41.653
♪ That's the brightest
it can shine ♪

1:30:41.740 --> 1:30:44.047
♪ And then when
it's setting down ♪

1:30:44.134 --> 1:30:47.659
♪ The colors blaze
and taste like wine ♪

1:30:47.746 --> 1:30:49.444
♪ And then when it's gone ♪

1:30:49.531 --> 1:30:53.186
♪ It shines through moonlight ♪

1:30:53.273 --> 1:30:58.191
♪ Reminding me she's fine ♪

1:30:59.889 --> 1:31:03.022
♪ Okay ♪

1:31:03.109 --> 1:31:06.461
♪ Nothing lasts forever ♪

1:31:20.475 --> 1:31:22.477
[Crickets chirping]

1:31:32.269 --> 1:31:33.836
- I've got to get
out of these shoes.

1:31:33.923 --> 1:31:34.967
My feet are killing me.

1:31:37.970 --> 1:31:41.060
Come on boy, unless you
plan on sleeping in the car.

1:31:50.983 --> 1:31:52.811
Oh, there's no room
for that thing in here.

1:31:52.898 --> 1:31:54.944
Just come back and get
what you want later.

1:32:10.612 --> 1:32:11.656
Home sweet home.

1:32:13.266 --> 1:32:15.094
I know it's not the
palace you're used to,

1:32:15.181 --> 1:32:16.400
but make yourself at home.

1:32:18.707 --> 1:32:19.795
Eat whatever you like.

1:32:45.603 --> 1:32:47.344
I have to go see after
a business matter.

1:32:47.431 --> 1:32:48.954
- You're leaving?

1:32:49.041 --> 1:32:50.565
- Well I told you mama's
got things to take care of.

1:32:50.652 --> 1:32:51.391
- I can come with you.

1:32:51.478 --> 1:32:52.262
- Not this time.

1:33:15.894 --> 1:33:18.027
[Ominous music]

1:33:20.116 --> 1:33:21.770
- Jess, get out here.

1:33:25.077 --> 1:33:26.992
[banging]

1:33:27.079 --> 1:33:29.429
Don't mess with me,
I'm not in the mood.

1:33:35.044 --> 1:33:35.958
Who are you?

1:33:36.045 --> 1:33:37.002
- I'm Finch.

1:33:37.089 --> 1:33:37.829
- Where's Jessica?

1:33:37.916 --> 1:33:38.656
- She's not here.

1:33:41.659 --> 1:33:42.442
You her boy?

1:33:44.749 --> 1:33:45.881
She said she had a kid,
but I didn't believe her.

1:33:47.447 --> 1:33:49.711
Don't believe much what
comes out of her mouth.

1:33:51.147 --> 1:33:53.802
She's telling the
truth about you though,

1:33:53.889 --> 1:33:55.020
you look just like her.

1:33:57.196 --> 1:33:59.068
How old are you, boy?

1:33:59.155 --> 1:33:59.938
- I'm 16.

1:34:00.809 --> 1:34:02.637
- Minor, huh?

1:34:02.724 --> 1:34:05.204
All right then, that'll do,

1:34:06.249 --> 1:34:07.424
that'll do very nicely.

1:34:08.947 --> 1:34:10.645
You see your mama,
she owes me some money

1:34:12.211 --> 1:34:14.736
and I don't think I'm
gonna get that money back.

1:34:14.823 --> 1:34:17.390
I do got some work you
can do for me though

1:34:17.477 --> 1:34:19.175
earn that money back.

1:34:19.262 --> 1:34:20.655
Wouldn't that be the
right thing to do,

1:34:20.742 --> 1:34:21.481
earn that money
back for your mama?

1:34:21.568 --> 1:34:22.352
- Yes, sir.

1:34:23.266 --> 1:34:24.049
- All right then.

1:34:25.007 --> 1:34:26.312
Put your shoes on.

1:34:26.399 --> 1:34:27.662
Get in the truck,
let's get to work.

1:34:27.749 --> 1:34:29.141
- Bobby, what are
you doing here?

1:34:29.228 --> 1:34:31.187
I told you I'd meet
you at the truck stop.

1:34:31.274 --> 1:34:32.710
- I was just chatting
with your boy here

1:34:32.797 --> 1:34:34.451
and he agreed to
work off your debt.

1:34:34.538 --> 1:34:37.062
- No, now get out of here.

1:34:37.149 --> 1:34:38.803
You won't have anything
to do with that boy.

1:34:38.890 --> 1:34:40.239
He's off limits, you got that?

1:34:40.326 --> 1:34:42.633
- I'm not waiting for
the money anymore, Jess.

1:34:42.720 --> 1:34:45.070
- You'll get your money double,

1:34:45.157 --> 1:34:46.550
but I'll need another week.

1:34:47.594 --> 1:34:49.074
- [Bobby] Double, yeah right?

1:34:49.161 --> 1:34:50.554
Come on boy, hurry up.

1:34:50.641 --> 1:34:54.819
- You will double,
no triple, next week.

1:34:54.906 --> 1:34:57.082
Pretty soon, money's not gonna
be a problem for me anymore.

1:34:57.169 --> 1:34:58.954
- [Bobby] You're a
lousy liar, Jess,

1:34:59.041 --> 1:34:59.998
you always have been.

1:35:00.085 --> 1:35:01.783
- Laugh it up, Bobby.

1:35:01.870 --> 1:35:04.437
But pretty soon, I'm not
gonna need you anymore.

1:35:04.524 --> 1:35:06.744
My son's got property
worth millions

1:35:06.831 --> 1:35:08.224
and after we sell it,

1:35:08.311 --> 1:35:10.139
we're taking off and
never looking back.

1:35:11.531 --> 1:35:13.359
[Dramatic music]

1:35:15.144 --> 1:35:17.189
- [Bobby] You're
a dreamer, Jess,

1:35:17.276 --> 1:35:19.104
with your heads all
up in them clouds.

1:35:21.106 --> 1:35:22.891
Dreaming gets people hurt.

1:35:27.112 --> 1:35:30.028
Look, I'll give
you a few more days

1:35:30.115 --> 1:35:32.857
but if you don't come up
with double what you owe me,

1:35:32.944 --> 1:35:34.119
then the boy's mine.

1:35:37.775 --> 1:35:39.777
Don't think about running off.

1:35:39.864 --> 1:35:41.170
I will come find you.

1:35:42.998 --> 1:35:44.129
[door slams]

1:35:44.216 --> 1:35:46.001
[engine starts up]

1:35:47.176 --> 1:35:48.960
- Finch, Finch.

1:35:49.047 --> 1:35:51.136
[knocking on door]

1:35:51.223 --> 1:35:53.051
Finch?

1:35:53.138 --> 1:35:54.966
That man didn't hurt you did he?

1:35:55.053 --> 1:35:56.620
Finch!

1:35:56.707 --> 1:35:59.492
[banging on door]

1:36:07.587 --> 1:36:09.415
[knocking]

1:36:12.244 --> 1:36:15.030
- Hey, your mom and I have
to go down to the courthouse

1:36:15.117 --> 1:36:15.900
to sign some papers.

1:36:17.336 --> 1:36:19.730
Finch's custody
hearing is today.

1:36:19.817 --> 1:36:22.080
Keep an eye out
for Jack and Lisa?

1:36:22.167 --> 1:36:22.907
- Yeah.

1:36:29.174 --> 1:36:31.829
- Toby, about what
you said the other day

1:36:31.916 --> 1:36:33.091
about Jack and Finch,

1:36:34.745 --> 1:36:39.054
I didn't know that's how
you felt and I should have.

1:36:39.141 --> 1:36:41.796
I should have paid
more attention to you

1:36:41.883 --> 1:36:44.624
and heard what you were trying
to tell me in different ways.

1:36:46.365 --> 1:36:48.498
Sometimes it has to be
just us, doesn't it?

1:36:51.022 --> 1:36:54.243
You have to know that you could
never be replaced as my son.

1:36:55.461 --> 1:36:57.028
I will always be proud of you.

1:36:58.682 --> 1:36:59.814
- I'm not.

1:37:06.995 --> 1:37:08.126
- That's Finch's journal.

1:37:09.127 --> 1:37:10.259
- I took it from him.

1:37:11.347 --> 1:37:12.696
I let him think I burned it.

1:37:12.783 --> 1:37:14.176
- What?

1:37:14.263 --> 1:37:16.004
- I was mad at him
for losing your book,

1:37:16.091 --> 1:37:18.658
so I let him think
that he lost his.

1:37:18.745 --> 1:37:20.095
- Toby.

1:37:20.182 --> 1:37:22.314
- I thought he was taking
everything from me,

1:37:22.401 --> 1:37:26.536
my friends, my family, you.

1:37:26.623 --> 1:37:28.146
- Hey, hey,

1:37:29.844 --> 1:37:33.195
nobody's ever gonna
take me away from you.

1:37:35.197 --> 1:37:36.807
Last night, I
looked through this

1:37:36.894 --> 1:37:39.462
and I saw this Bible verse
he wrote in the first page

1:37:39.549 --> 1:37:41.638
about trials testing your faith

1:37:41.725 --> 1:37:43.466
and making you more complete

1:37:43.553 --> 1:37:44.946
and that people without faith,

1:37:45.033 --> 1:37:47.339
just get tossed
around by the wind.

1:37:47.426 --> 1:37:48.993
And that's how I feel right now,

1:37:49.080 --> 1:37:50.995
like my feet can't
even find the ground.

1:37:52.736 --> 1:37:55.086
- Yeah, I know that feeling.

1:37:57.219 --> 1:38:00.265
I felt that way when I quit
my job and started writing.

1:38:00.352 --> 1:38:01.005
- Really?

1:38:02.137 --> 1:38:03.878
- Everyone thought I was crazy

1:38:03.965 --> 1:38:07.011
to leave something so sure
for something so uncertain.

1:38:08.491 --> 1:38:10.972
Except your mom,
she believes in me.

1:38:12.234 --> 1:38:13.235
- I do too.

1:38:16.107 --> 1:38:19.067
- You know, I think we'll
both feel more grounded

1:38:19.154 --> 1:38:20.546
if we worry less

1:38:20.633 --> 1:38:23.027
about what other people's
opinions of us are

1:38:23.114 --> 1:38:24.942
and focus more on God's.

1:38:26.683 --> 1:38:28.903
- It can't be too good about me.

1:38:28.990 --> 1:38:31.906
- Hey, you will always
be his kind of kid.

1:38:31.993 --> 1:38:33.908
Nothing you do will change that.

1:38:39.783 --> 1:38:41.480
- I want to fix this.

1:38:44.222 --> 1:38:45.745
- You could ask God.

1:38:46.659 --> 1:38:48.792
Just keep it simple.

1:38:50.228 --> 1:38:53.057
Many times he gives
simple answers.

1:38:55.233 --> 1:38:57.235
- You learned that
from Finch, didn't you?

1:38:58.193 --> 1:39:00.195
- His gran actually,

1:39:00.282 --> 1:39:02.937
a woman I would never want to
anger while she's knitting.

1:39:07.376 --> 1:39:10.901
- Dad, I want to go to
the courthouse with you

1:39:10.988 --> 1:39:14.818
but I need a minute
first to ask a question.

1:39:16.994 --> 1:39:19.736
- Okay then, you take a minute,

1:39:19.823 --> 1:39:20.824
I'll go get the car.

1:39:23.783 --> 1:39:26.438
- And thanks for talking to me.

1:39:29.180 --> 1:39:30.181
- Anytime.

1:39:42.106 --> 1:39:45.544
- Your client is 20 minutes
late to her own custody hearing.

1:39:45.631 --> 1:39:49.070
Mr. Billings, any explanation?

1:39:49.157 --> 1:39:52.073
- I'm sure there was just a
traffic problem, your honor.

1:39:52.160 --> 1:39:54.901
Perhaps we can
reconvene tomorrow.

1:39:54.989 --> 1:39:57.469
- I'm not your
dentist, Mr. Billings.

1:39:57.556 --> 1:40:00.472
I do not have another opening
on my docket until July.

1:40:00.559 --> 1:40:02.126
We can reconvene them.

1:40:02.213 --> 1:40:04.781
- I don't believe that would
be in the best interest

1:40:04.868 --> 1:40:07.001
of the mother or the child.

1:40:07.088 --> 1:40:08.350
- Mr. Billings.

1:40:08.437 --> 1:40:09.481
[knocking]

1:40:09.568 --> 1:40:11.222
- We can proceed, your honor.

1:40:20.927 --> 1:40:22.320
You're late.

1:40:22.407 --> 1:40:24.192
- She wouldn't come unless
I got her a new dress.

1:40:24.279 --> 1:40:26.194
[sighs]

1:40:26.281 --> 1:40:28.370
- Nice of you to
join us, Miss Hague.

1:40:28.457 --> 1:40:29.371
- It's nice to be here.

1:40:30.894 --> 1:40:32.461
- In the matter of custody

1:40:32.548 --> 1:40:36.682
of the minor here after referred
to as "Finch Whittaker."

1:40:36.769 --> 1:40:37.857
- Hague.

1:40:37.944 --> 1:40:39.424
- I'm sorry?

1:40:39.511 --> 1:40:41.948
- Finch Hague,
that's his name now.

1:40:42.036 --> 1:40:42.993
- Miss Hague-

1:40:43.080 --> 1:40:43.994
[knocking]

1:40:44.081 --> 1:40:45.604
Were we expecting anyone else?

1:40:47.215 --> 1:40:49.347
- Judge Raymond, I am
so sorry to interrupt.

1:40:49.434 --> 1:40:52.394
My husband, Keith and I
are Finch's foster parents.

1:40:52.481 --> 1:40:55.223
- Deputy Brennan, I
appreciate you coming by,

1:40:55.310 --> 1:40:56.789
but the foster parents

1:40:56.876 --> 1:40:58.182
are not required to be
here for this hearing.

1:40:58.269 --> 1:41:00.054
You can sign your
papers out front.

1:41:00.141 --> 1:41:02.665
- If I could, there
is something I,

1:41:02.752 --> 1:41:04.797
my family and I
would like to say.

1:41:04.884 --> 1:41:06.277
- I object, your honor.

1:41:06.364 --> 1:41:08.540
This woman has a personal
interest in this matter

1:41:08.627 --> 1:41:10.673
and would do anything to
stop these proceedings.

1:41:10.760 --> 1:41:12.022
- I'm afraid this really

1:41:12.109 --> 1:41:13.763
isn't the appropriate
time, Janelle.

1:41:13.850 --> 1:41:15.199
It'll have to wait.

1:41:15.286 --> 1:41:17.245
- It is very important
that we speak to Finch.

1:41:17.332 --> 1:41:19.247
- This isn't the time.

1:41:19.334 --> 1:41:21.118
Who are all these people?

1:41:21.205 --> 1:41:22.076
- This is my family.

1:41:22.163 --> 1:41:24.034
- I object, your honor.

1:41:24.121 --> 1:41:25.818
- Pipe down, we're not in court.

1:41:25.905 --> 1:41:27.864
- Your honor, before
you make a ruling,

1:41:27.951 --> 1:41:30.736
Finch needs to know that
we don't want him to go.

1:41:30.823 --> 1:41:32.564
- You see Finch has become
a part of our family

1:41:32.651 --> 1:41:34.044
and we can't lose him.

1:41:34.131 --> 1:41:35.915
- And I need him to
teach me how to hunt.

1:41:36.002 --> 1:41:38.004
- This is highly irregular.

1:41:38.092 --> 1:41:40.137
- Your honor, I lied to him.

1:41:40.224 --> 1:41:42.183
I told him that he didn't
belong at our house

1:41:42.270 --> 1:41:43.967
and that we weren't his family.

1:41:44.054 --> 1:41:45.969
But in a way we kind of are.

1:41:46.056 --> 1:41:47.666
You see, we fight like brothers.

1:41:47.753 --> 1:41:50.626
I let him believe
that I burned this,

1:41:50.713 --> 1:41:53.107
but I was wrong about a
lot of things, your honor.

1:41:53.194 --> 1:41:55.109
So will you please
tell Finch for me

1:41:55.196 --> 1:41:56.806
how sorry I am

1:41:56.893 --> 1:42:00.026
and that if he wants to stay
with us, that's fine with me.

1:42:00.114 --> 1:42:01.637
- I object, your honor.

1:42:01.724 --> 1:42:02.942
They're just saying
everything to you

1:42:03.029 --> 1:42:04.640
that they want to say to him.

1:42:04.727 --> 1:42:05.771
Now I move for a mistrial.

1:42:05.858 --> 1:42:07.817
- For the last time, Billings,

1:42:07.904 --> 1:42:10.602
this is not a trial,
it's a custody hearing.

1:42:10.689 --> 1:42:13.170
You can't declare a
mistrial of a hearing.

1:42:16.130 --> 1:42:20.177
Young man, did you happen
to hear everything they said

1:42:20.264 --> 1:42:21.874
or do I have to repeat it?

1:42:21.961 --> 1:42:23.267
- I heard it, your honor.

1:42:23.354 --> 1:42:25.008
- Good.

1:42:25.095 --> 1:42:26.879
Now listen to me, all of you,

1:42:28.098 --> 1:42:29.317
I appreciate you
coming down here

1:42:29.404 --> 1:42:30.666
and I'm certain that Finch here

1:42:30.753 --> 1:42:33.538
has benefited from
everything you've said,

1:42:33.625 --> 1:42:36.628
but unfortunately
the law is the law.

1:42:36.715 --> 1:42:39.022
Miss Hague is seeking
full custody of her son

1:42:39.109 --> 1:42:41.285
and since she is his
biological mother,

1:42:41.372 --> 1:42:43.200
the law protects her rights.

1:42:45.115 --> 1:42:47.900
And I am certain that you
are a very fine young man

1:42:47.987 --> 1:42:51.252
to have won the hearts of
all of these good people

1:42:51.339 --> 1:42:52.992
and I wish it were in my power

1:42:53.079 --> 1:42:54.516
to let you choose where
you'd like to live

1:42:54.603 --> 1:42:56.387
but according to the
laws of this state,

1:42:57.432 --> 1:42:58.607
that is not a factor either.

1:43:00.304 --> 1:43:02.654
I have no choice but to grant
Miss Hague full custody.

1:43:02.741 --> 1:43:05.222
- Well said, your honor.

1:43:05.309 --> 1:43:09.357
- Mr. Billings, I don't
like what I smell here.

1:43:09.444 --> 1:43:10.836
The law's on your
side this time,

1:43:10.923 --> 1:43:13.187
but you don't want to
cross my path again.

1:43:14.536 --> 1:43:17.103
[ominous music]

1:43:21.238 --> 1:43:23.414
- I'm sorry I can't
give you back your bird.

1:43:25.677 --> 1:43:27.636
- Thanks for this.

1:43:27.723 --> 1:43:31.161
- You were right about me
leaving my family behind.

1:43:31.248 --> 1:43:34.208
I was just being stupid
and I won't do it again.

1:43:35.209 --> 1:43:38.603
- Good, they need you.

1:43:40.518 --> 1:43:42.825
- Problem is we need you too.

1:43:45.175 --> 1:43:47.743
Dad's right, you
should keep on writing.

1:43:47.830 --> 1:43:49.266
He should know, he's
one of the best.

1:43:50.876 --> 1:43:53.183
I think you'll be a
great writer one day.

1:43:53.270 --> 1:43:54.140
- You think so?

1:43:54.228 --> 1:43:55.403
- I know so.

1:43:55.490 --> 1:43:57.361
- Your honor, I object.

1:43:57.448 --> 1:43:58.884
- What are you doing?

1:43:58.971 --> 1:44:01.060
- Miss Hague, I'm afraid
you don't understand.

1:44:01.147 --> 1:44:02.975
- I do understand.

1:44:03.062 --> 1:44:05.717
I understand that this
family loves my son

1:44:05.804 --> 1:44:07.415
and he loves them.

1:44:07.502 --> 1:44:09.852
- Your honor, my client has
not consulted with her counsel.

1:44:09.939 --> 1:44:12.333
- That's because I'm firing
my counsel, your honor.

1:44:13.986 --> 1:44:16.641
- I need a moment
alone with my client.

1:44:16.728 --> 1:44:19.209
She doesn't understand
how these things work.

1:44:19.296 --> 1:44:21.516
- I believe she
does, Mr. Billings.

1:44:21.603 --> 1:44:23.779
- Don't get me
wrong, I love Finch

1:44:23.866 --> 1:44:26.216
I really do, but I'm
not fit to care for him.

1:44:26.303 --> 1:44:27.913
You see, I got problems

1:44:28.000 --> 1:44:30.133
that have chased me around
my whole life, your honor

1:44:30.220 --> 1:44:32.222
and I can't shake
'em, yet anyway,

1:44:32.309 --> 1:44:34.572
but it's not the kind of
life I want for my son.

1:44:36.008 --> 1:44:38.272
My son is gonna
be a great writer,

1:44:39.969 --> 1:44:42.580
but if he stays with me,
he might not get there.

1:44:44.452 --> 1:44:45.061
- I see.

1:44:46.454 --> 1:44:48.456
Well based on this
new information,

1:44:48.543 --> 1:44:49.805
Mr and Mrs. Brennan,

1:44:49.892 --> 1:44:51.154
are you willing
to resume the role

1:44:51.241 --> 1:44:52.764
of foster parenting for Finch?

1:44:52.851 --> 1:44:54.244
- We are, your honor.
- Yes.

1:44:54.331 --> 1:44:56.028
- No your honor,
that's not good enough.

1:44:56.115 --> 1:44:58.988
Finch needs a stable
home that he can rely on.

1:44:59.075 --> 1:45:00.511
And for once in my life,

1:45:00.598 --> 1:45:02.339
I'm gonna be the one
who gives it to him.

1:45:02.426 --> 1:45:04.385
I wish to sign away
my parental rights

1:45:04.472 --> 1:45:07.301
so that Finch can
be properly adopted.

1:45:07.388 --> 1:45:09.390
- All right then.

1:45:09.477 --> 1:45:11.087
Mr and Mrs. Brennan,

1:45:11.174 --> 1:45:13.698
are you willing to become
adoptive parents to Finch?

1:45:15.265 --> 1:45:18.050
- Finch, what do you say?

1:45:19.095 --> 1:45:21.184
- What about Bobby?

1:45:21.271 --> 1:45:23.578
- Don't you worry
about anything.

1:45:23.665 --> 1:45:24.318
I'll handle him.

1:45:25.710 --> 1:45:28.887
Do this for me,
it's what I want.

1:45:33.501 --> 1:45:34.284
- Yes.

1:45:35.807 --> 1:45:37.243
- We all agree, your honor.

1:45:37.331 --> 1:45:39.071
- Then it's settled.

1:45:39.158 --> 1:45:40.682
The Brennan's will
retain full custody

1:45:40.769 --> 1:45:42.466
with clearance to
proceed with adoption

1:45:42.553 --> 1:45:44.250
effective immediately.

1:45:44.338 --> 1:45:47.123
[inspiring music]

1:45:54.260 --> 1:45:55.044
- Jessica,

1:45:57.612 --> 1:46:00.179
I don't know what to say.

1:46:00.266 --> 1:46:03.052
- Say you'll help him become
everything he's meant to be.

1:46:03.139 --> 1:46:06.490
- Only if you promise to get
better and help us do it.

1:46:07.796 --> 1:46:10.538
[inspiring music]

1:46:16.457 --> 1:46:18.372
[Birds chirping]

1:46:22.767 --> 1:46:25.248
[inspiring music]

1:46:40.568 --> 1:46:43.353
[Lisa] The first thing they
ought to put in her is a road.

1:46:43.440 --> 1:46:46.443
- No, walking is half the fun.

1:46:47.313 --> 1:46:48.227
- I like hiking.

1:46:49.359 --> 1:46:50.926
- We're almost there.

1:46:51.013 --> 1:46:54.190
[gentle string music]

1:47:02.198 --> 1:47:04.069
- This place is so cool.

1:47:04.156 --> 1:47:05.549
Can we come here every weekend?

1:47:07.159 --> 1:47:08.247
- We could stay here next summer

1:47:08.334 --> 1:47:09.727
while dad writes his next book.

1:47:09.814 --> 1:47:11.250
- Next book?

1:47:11.337 --> 1:47:13.688
- Oh my brother Jerry
recovered the file.

1:47:13.775 --> 1:47:16.342
I sent my book into the
publisher this morning on time.

1:47:16.430 --> 1:47:17.169
- That's great.

1:47:17.256 --> 1:47:18.301
- Yeah.

1:47:20.825 --> 1:47:22.523
- Oh, I almost forgot,

1:47:23.349 --> 1:47:24.742
I got you this

1:47:24.829 --> 1:47:27.136
in honor of the adoption
being official and all.

1:47:27.223 --> 1:47:29.921
I tried to carve on myself,
but it looked like roadkill.

1:47:31.183 --> 1:47:32.924
I know it's not your gran's but-

1:47:33.011 --> 1:47:36.362
- No, it's better
than my gran's.

1:47:37.973 --> 1:47:40.889
When I looked at that
one, I thought of her,

1:47:40.976 --> 1:47:43.761
but when I look at this one,
I'll think of both of you.

1:47:46.460 --> 1:47:47.896
- There's some cleaning to do

1:47:47.983 --> 1:47:50.028
but we'll have it up
and going in no time.

1:47:50.115 --> 1:47:51.900
- I think it's beautiful here.

1:47:51.987 --> 1:47:54.337
- To the Whittaker family cabin.

1:47:54.424 --> 1:47:57.166
- No, to the Brennan
family cabin.

1:48:02.214 --> 1:48:05.783
[gentle string music]

1:48:09.874 --> 1:48:12.007
[all laughing]

1:48:16.664 --> 1:48:19.188
- [Keith] Oh no, no, no!

1:48:21.843 --> 1:48:23.279
[Upbeat music]

1:48:29.372 --> 1:48:32.114
♪ There's nothing
like a good smile ♪

1:48:32.201 --> 1:48:34.246
♪ To give your heart a break ♪

1:48:34.333 --> 1:48:36.335
♪ Nothing like this
peace of mind ♪

1:48:36.422 --> 1:48:38.686
♪ To feel that type of way ♪

1:48:38.773 --> 1:48:42.907
♪ Some days I can see that ♪
it's all drifting away ♪

1:48:42.994 --> 1:48:45.127
♪ Like the memories
of an old love ♪

1:48:45.214 --> 1:48:46.998
♪ Make you feel
that type of way ♪

1:48:47.085 --> 1:48:49.523
♪ I throw my head back ♪

1:48:49.610 --> 1:48:52.221
♪ And soak up these
summer rays of gold ♪

1:48:52.308 --> 1:48:56.007
♪ All these summer
rays of gold ♪

1:48:56.094 --> 1:48:59.054
♪ I'm sitting here
looking at you ♪

1:48:59.141 --> 1:49:00.969
♪ I'm laughing out
loud to myself ♪

1:49:01.056 --> 1:49:04.842
♪ 'Cause I know one
day we'll be old ♪

1:49:04.929 --> 1:49:06.931
♪ So we tear across
the county line ♪

